obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (40397)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40397&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act, may be called the Manipur Municipalities`
  line `Act, 1994.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of the State of Manipur except the Hill Areas to which the Manipur`
  line `(Hill Areas) District Council Act, 1971 (Manipur Act 76 of 1971) extends or any area which is included`
  line `in a Cantonment under the Cantonment Act, 1924 (2 of 1924).`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 24th day of May, 1994.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (40398)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40398&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(1) "Adhyaksha" means an Adhyaksha of a Zilla Parishad elected under the provisions of the`
  line `Manipur Panchayati Raj Act, 1994 (26 of 1994);`
  line
  line `(2) "building" means a house, out house, stable, latrine, urinal, shed, hut, wall (other than a`
  line `boundary wall) or any other structure, whether of masonry, bricks, wood, mud, metal or other`
  line `material but does not include any portable shelter;`
  line
  line `(3) "bye-law" means a bye-law made under this Act by notification;`
  line
  line `(4) "Committee" means a Committee other than a Ward Committee constituted under this Act;`
  line
  line `(5) "compound" means land whether enclosed or not, which is the appurtenance of a building or`
  line `the common appurtenance of several buildings;`
  line
  line `(6) "conservancy" means the removal and disposal of sewage, offensive matter and rubbish;`
  line
  line `(7) "Corporation" means a Municipal Corporation;`
  line
  line `(8) "Council" means a Municipal Council;`
  line
  line `(9) "Councillor" means a member of a Municipal Council or Nagar Panchayat, as the case may`
  line `be, elected or appointed under this Act;`
  line
  line `(10) "Deputy Commissioner" means the Deputy Commissioner of a district of Manipur having`
  line `jurisdiction over the Municipality, or any other officer at any time appointed by the Government to`
  line `perform, in any district or districts the functions of a Deputy Commissioner under this Act;`
  line
  line `(11) "Director" means the Director of Municipal Administration, Housing and Urban`
  line `Development of the Government of Manipur or such other officer as may be appointed by the`
  line `Government to exercise the functions of the Director of Municipal Administration, Housing and`
  line `Urban Development of Manipur;`
  line
  line `(12) "district" means a district in the State of Manipur;`
  line
  line `(13) "District Magistrate" means the District Magistrate and includes the Additional District`
  line `Magistrate or any such Magistrate as may be appointed in this behalf by the Government, having`
  line `territorial jurisdiction over the Municipality;`
  line
  line `(14) "drain" includes a sewer, a house-drain, a drain of any other description, a tunnel, a culvert, a`
  line `ditch, a channel and any other device for carrying off sullage, sewage, offensive matter, polluted`
  line `water, waste water, rain water or subsoil water;`
  line
  line `(15) "Election Commission" means the State Election Commission constituted under section 98`
  line `of the Manipur Panchayati Raj Act, 1994 (26 of 1994);`
  line
  line `(16) "Executive Officer" means Executive Officer of a municipality appointed under this Act;`
  line
  line `(17) "financial year" means the year commencing on the 1st day of April of a year and ending on`
  line `31st day of March of the succeeding year;`
  line
  line `(18) "food" includes every article used for food or drink by man other than drugs or water, and`
  line `any article which ordinarily enters into or used in the composition or preparation of human food and`
  line `also includes confectionery, flavouring and colouring matter, spices and condiments;`
  line
  line `(19) "Government" means the State Government of Manipur;`
  line
  line `(20) "half-year" means a half-year commencing on the 1st day of April or the 1st day of October,`
  line `or such other date as the State Government may, by notification, appoint;`
  line
  line `(21) "holding" means land held under one title or agreement and surrounded by one set of`
  line `boundaries:`
  line
  line `Provided that where two or more adjoining holdings form part and parcel of the site or premises`
  line `of a dwelling-house, manufactory, warehouse or place of trade or business, such holdings shall be`
  line `deemed to be one holding for the purposes of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where land has been let out to occupants in separate parcels paying rent`
  line `separately, each such parcel shall be treated as a distinct holding in spite of such parcels of land being`
  line `held under one title.`
  line
  line `Explanation I.--Holdings separated by a road or other means of communication shall be deemed`
  line `to be adjoining within the meaning of this proviso.`
  line
  line `Explanation II.--Any plot of land having clear boundaries and lying entirely vacant, if fit for`
  line `building purposes or if yielding any income, shall when not appurtenant to any agricultural purposes,`
  line `be regarded as a "holding";`
  line
  line `(22) "house" means any hut, shop, warehouse, workshop, masonry or framed;`
  line
  line `(23) "house-gully" or "service passage" means a passage or strip of land constructed, set apart or`
  line `utilised, for the purpose of serving as or carrying a drain or affording access to a latrine, privy, urinal,`
  line `cess-pool or other receptacle of filthy or polluted matter by municipal employees or other persons`
  line `employed in the cleansing thereof or in the removal of such matter therefrom, and includes the`
  line `air-space above such passage or land;`
  line
  line `(24) " hut" means any building, which is constructed principally of wood, bamboo, mud, leaves,`
  line `grass or thatch and includes any temporary structure of whatever size or any small building of`
  line `whatever material made;`
  line
  line `(25) "infectious or contagious disease" means cholera, plague, small-pox, chicken-pox,`
  line `kala-azar, tuberculosis, diphtheria and typhoid or enteric fever or such other dangerous disease as the`
  line `Government may notify in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(26) "inhabitant" used with reference to a local area means any person ordinarily residing or`
  line `carrying on business or owning or occupying immovable property therein;`
  line
  line `(27) "joint family" means a family of which the members live together, have a common mess and`
  line `are descendants from a common ancestor and shall include wives or husbands, as the case may be, of`
  line `its members, but shall exclude married daughters and their children;`
  line
  line `(28) "land" includes benefits arising out of land, houses and things attached to the earth or`
  line `permanently fastened to anything attached to the earth and also land covered by water;`
  line
  line `(29) "Legislative Assembly" means the Legislative Assembly of Manipur;`
  line
  line `(30) "Local Authority" includes District Council, Municipal Council, Nagar Panchayat,`
  line `Municipal Corporation and Panchayat;`
  line
  line `(31) "lodging house" means a house in which visitors or other persons are lodged on hire for a`
  line `night or more;`
  line
  line `(32) "market" or "bazar" means any place, by whatever name called, where persons assemble for`
  line `the sale of meat, fish, fruit, vegetables, live stock or any other article of food or merchandise, declared`
  line `and licensed by the municipality as a market;`
  line
  line `(33) "municipal area" means the territorial area of a municipality as is notified by the Governor;`
  line
  line `(34) "municipality" means the Nagar Panchayat or the Municipal Council, as the case may be,`
  line `constituted under the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(35) "municipal market" means a market belonging to or maintained by the municipality;`
  line
  line `(36) "notification" means notification in the Official Gazette of Manipur;`
  line
  line `(37) "nuisance" includes any act, omission, place or thing which causes or is likely to cause`
  line `injury, danger, annoyance or offence to the sense or sight, smelling or hearing or disturbance to rest`
  line `or sleep or which is or may be, dangerous to life or injurious to health or property;`
  line
  line `(38) "occupier" includes--`
  line
  line `(a) any person who is paying or is liable to pay to the owner the rent or any portion of the rent`
  line `of the land or building in respect of which such rent is paid or is payable;`
  line
  line `(b) an owner in occupation of or otherwise using his own land or building;`
  line
  line `(c) a rent free tenant of any land or building;`
  line
  line `(d) a licensee in occupation of any land or building; and`
  line
  line `(e) any person who is liable to pay to the owner of land or building damages for the use and`
  line `occupation of such land or building;`
  line
  line `(39) "offensive matter" includes animal, carcases, kitchen or stable refuse, dung, dirt, putrid or`
  line `putrefying substance and filth of any kind which is not included in sewage;`
  line
  line `(40) "owner" includes--`
  line
  line `(a) a person who for the time being is receiving or is entitled to receive, the rent of any land`
  line `or building or of any part of any land or building whether on his own account or on account of`
  line `himself and others or as an agent, trustee for any person or society or for any religious or`
  line `charitable purpose, guardian or as a receiver or who would so receive such rent or be entitled to`
  line `receive it if the land, building or part thereof were let to a tenant, and`
  line
  line `(b) the head of a Government department in respect of properties under their respective`
  line control;
  line
  line `(41) "Panchayat" means an institution of self-government at the district or village level`
  line `constituted under the Manipur Panchayati Raj Act, 1994 (26 of 1994);`
  line
  line `(42) "platform" means any structure which is placed on or covers or projects over, any public`
  line `road or any open drain, sewer or aqueduct;`
  line
  line `(43) "population" means the population as ascertained at the last preceding census of which the`
  line `relevant figures have been published;`
  line
  line `(44) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(45) "private road" means any street, road, square, court alley or passage which is not a public`
  line `road and includes a pathway made by the owner or premises on his own land to secure access to, or`
  line `the convenient use of, such premises;`
  line
  line `(46) the expression "re-erect" when used with reference to building, includes--`
  line
  line `(a) the reconstruction of a building after more than one-half of its cubical extent has been`
  line `taken down or burnt down or has fallen down;`
  line
  line `(b) the conversion of one or more huts or temporary structures into a masonry or framed`
  line building;
  line
  line `(c) the conversion into place for human habitation of any building not originally constructed`
  line `for such habitation; and`
  line
  line `(d) the extension of a building;`
  line
  line `(47) "private slaughter house" means a slaughter house which is not a municipal slaughter house;`
  line
  line `(48) "public place" means a space, not being private property which is open to the use or`
  line `enjoyment of the public whether such space is vested in a municipality or not;`
  line
  line `(49) "public road" means any street, road, square, court alley, passage or pathway over which the`
  line `public have a right of way whether a thoroughfare or not, and includes--`
  line
  line `(a) the roadway over any public bridge or causeway;`
  line
  line `(b) the footway attached to any such road, public bridge or causeway; and`
  line
  line `(c) the drains attached to any such road, public bridge or causeway, and the land, whether`
  line `covered or not by any pavement, verandah or other structure, which lies on either side of the`
  line `roadway up to the boundaries of the adjacent property whether that property is private property or`
  line `Government property;`
  line
  line `(50) "regulation" means a regulation made by the municipality under this Act, by notification;`
  line
  line `(51) "rubbish" means ashes, broken brick, mortar, broken glass, dust or refuse of any kind which`
  line `is not filth;`
  line
  line `(52) "rule" means a rule made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(53) "Scheduled Castes" means such castes, races or tribes or parts of groups within such castes,`
  line `tribes as are specified to be Scheduled Castes, in relation to the State of Manipur under article 341 of`
  line `the Constitution of India;`
  line
  line `(54) "Scheduled Tribes" means such tribes or tribal communities or parts of groups within such`
  line `tribes or tribal communities as are specified to be Scheduled Tribes in relation to the State of Manipur`
  line `under article 342 of the Constitution of India;`
  line
  line `(55) "sewage" means night-soil and other contents of privies, latrines, urinals, cesspools and`
  line `drains, and includes polluted water from sink, bathrooms, stables, cattle-sheds and other like places`
  line `and also discharges from manufactories of all kinds;`
  line
  line `(56) "slaughter house" means any place ordinarily used for the slaughter of animals for the`
  line `purpose of selling the flesh thereof for human consumption;`
  line
  line `(57) "urban areas" means the areas in the State of Manipur which are not rural areas;`
  line
  line `(58) "vehicle" includes bicycles, tricycles and automotor cars and every wheeled conveyance`
  line `whether a carriage, cart, van, dray which is used or capable of being used on a public road;`
  line
  line `(59) "ward" means a municipal ward constituted under section 18;`
  line
  line `(60) "water works" includes all tanks, streams, cisterns, springs, pumps, wells, reservoirs,`
  line `aqueducts, sluices mains, pipes, hydrants, stand pipes and conduits and all lands, buildings,`
  line `machinery and things used for, or intended for the purpose of, supplying water;`
  line
  line `(61) "Zilla Parishad" means a Zilla Parishad of a district constituted under the Manipur`
  line `Panchayati Raj Act, 1994 (26 of 1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (40399)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Constitution of municipalities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40399&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Governor shall, by notification, constitute--`
  line
  line `(a) a Nagar Panchayat for a transitional area, that is to say, an area in transition from a rural area`
  line `to an urban area;`
  line
  line `(b) a Municipal Council for a smaller urban area; and`
  line
  line `(c) a Municipal Corporation for a larger urban area, in accordance with the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that a municipality under this section may not be constituted in such urban area or part`
  line `thereof as the Governor may, having regard to the size of the area and the municipal services being`
  line `provided or proposed to be provided by an industrial establishment in that area and such other factors as it`
  line `may deem fit, by notification, specify to be an industrial township.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section, "a transitional area", "a smaller urban area" or "a larger urban area"`
  line `means such areas as the Governor may, having regard to the population of the area, the density of the`
  line `population therein, the revenue generated for local administration, the percentage of employment in nonagricultural activities, the economic importance or such other factors as it may deem fit, specify by`
  line `notification for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), any local area, except in Scheduled Area,`
  line `which was declared as a small town or a municipality under the Manipur Municipalities Act, 1976`
  line `(Manipur Act 26 of 1976), before the commencement of this Act, shall be deemed to have been declared`
  line `as a transitional area or a smaller urban area, as the case may be, for the purpose of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Before issue of notification under sub-section (1) a draft of the notification is to be published`
  line `indicating local limits of the area to be included or excluded from the municipality.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person who is ordinarily resident of the local area in respect of which the draft notification`
  line `has been published under sub-section (3) may, object to the proposal contained in such notification in`
  line `writing to the Deputy Commissioner within forty-five days from the date of publication of the said draft`
  line notification.
  line
  line `(5) On receipt of the objection under sub-section (4), the Deputy Commissioner shall within`
  line `forty-five days of the receipt of objection forward the same with his comments to the Government for its`
  line consideration.
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (40400)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Effect of exclusion of local area from municipality.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40400&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a local area is excluded from a`
  line `municipality by a notification under sub-section (1) of section 3, and is included in the other local`
  line `authority the Government shall frame a scheme determining what portion of the balance of the municipal`
  line `fund and all other property vested in that municipality, shall, on such exclusion, vest--`
  line
  line `(i) when such area is included within the limits of any other local authority, in such authority; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in any other case, in the Government and in what manner the liability of the municipality shall`
  line `be apportioned between the municipality and such local authority or the Government, as the case may`
  line `be, and on the publication of such a scheme in the Official Gazette, such property and liability shall`
  line `vest and be apportioned accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that before framing of any such scheme, the Government shall consult the municipality`
  line `and where the area is included within the limits of any local authority, such authority also.`
  line
  line `(2) All money due to the municipality, immediately before the date of such exclusion on account of`
  line `tax, toll, fee, rate or otherwise may in respect of the areas so excluded be recovered by the municipality as`
  line `if such area has not been excluded.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (40401)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Election and maintenance of boundary marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40401&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Every municipality shall cause to be erected`
  line `and set up and maintain boundary marks defining the limits of the area subject to its authority as set out`
  line `by the notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (40402)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Incorporation of Nagar Panchayat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40402&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `A Nagar Panchayat shall be a body corporate by its name,`
  line `having a perpetual succession and a common seal with power to acquire, hold and dispose of property and`
  line `to contract, and shall sue and be sued in its name.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (40403)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Composition of Nagar Panchayat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40403&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Nagar Panchayat shall consist of such number of`
  line `Councillors as may be fixed by the Government from time to time by notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise provided in sub-section (3), all the seats in a Nagar Panchayat shall be filled by`
  line `persons chosen by direct election from the territorial constituencies to be known as wards in the municipal`
  line `area of Nagar Panchayat.`
  line
  line `(3) The Government may appoint a person having special knowledge or experience in municipal`
  line `administration to be a Councillor of the Nagar Panchayat:`
  line
  line `Provided that such person shall not have the right to vote in the meetings of the Nagar Panchayat.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (40404)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Application of certain provisions relating to Council in case of Nagar Panchayat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40404&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line The
  line `provisions of sections 17, 19 and 20 of this Act relating to Council shall also apply in case of Nagar`
  line Panchayat.
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (40405)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Chairperson and Vice-Chairperson of Nagar Panchayat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40405&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `For every Nagar Panchayat there`
  line `shall be a Chairperson and a Vice-Chairperson.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (40406)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Election of Chairperson and Vice-Chairpersons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40406&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in the Act,`
  line `the Councillors at the first meeting of the Nagar Panchayat to be called at the instance of the Deputy`
  line `Commissioner after a General Election shall elect one of them to be the Chairperson in accordance with`
  line `the rules made in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) An election under sub-section (1) shall take place--`
  line
  line `(a) within twenty-one days from the date of notification of the result under section 22;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of vacancy in the office of the Chairperson on account of any reason other than the`
  line `expiry of the term of office of the Chairperson, within twenty-one days from the date of the`
  line `occurrence of the vacancy.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government shall appoint a person to preside over the meeting and for the purpose of`
  line `the business mentioned in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) The Councillors shall, either at the meeting referred to in sub-section (1) or at any subsequent`
  line `meeting elect one among themselves, other than the Chairperson elected under sub-section (1), to be a`
  line Vice-Chairperson.
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (40407)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Resignation by Chairperson, Vice Chairperson and Councillor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40407&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson may`
  line `resign his office by writing under his hand addressed to the Executive Officer.`
  line
  line `(2) The Vice-Chairperson or a Councillor may resign his office by writing under his hand addressed`
  line `to the Chairperson, who shall forward it to the Executive Officer.`
  line
  line `(3) The resignation under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall take effect from the date on which it`
  line `is accepted by the Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The Executive Officer shall forthwith intimate the fact of resignation received under`
  line `sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) to the Nagar Panchayat and the State Government.`
  line
  line `(5) On receipt of intimation under sub-section (4) the State Government shall notify the fact of the`
  line `resignation and occurrence of casual vacancy consequent thereon.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (40408)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Remuneration to Chairperson and Vice-Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40408&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson or Vice-Chairperson`
  line `or any other Councillor of Nagar Panchayat may be granted by that Nagar Panchayat such remuneration`
  line `or such allowance as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (40409)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Incorporation of Municipal Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40409&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `A Municipal Council shall be a body corporate by its`
  line `name, having a perpetual succession and a common seal with power to acquire, hold and dispose of`
  line `property and to contract, and shall sue and be sued in its name.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (40410)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Municipal administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40410&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Except as otherwise provided in this Act, the municipal`
  line `administration of a municipality shall vest in the Council or the Nagar Panchayat, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (40411)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Composition of Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40411&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Council shall consist of such number of councillors as may`
  line `be fixed by the State Government from time to time by notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as provided in sub-section (3), all the seats in a municipality shall be filled by persons`
  line `chosen by direct election from the territorial constituencies to be known as wards in the municipal area.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government may appoint a person having special knowledge or experience in`
  line `Municipal administration to be a member of the Municipal Council:`
  line
  line `Provided that such person shall not have the right to vote in the meetings of the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (40412)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Constitution and composition of Wards Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40412&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) In respect of a municipality having`
  line `population of three lakhs or more there shall be constituted by the State Government, by order, such`
  line `number of Wards Committees as may be determined by it, so however, that each Wards Committee shall`
  line `consist of not less than five wards:`
  line
  line `Provided that in constituting Wards Committees, the State Government shall maintain geographical`
  line `contiguity as far as possible.`
  line
  line `(2) Each Wards Committee shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(i) the members elected from the wards for which Wards Committee is constituted;`
  line
  line `(ii) the Executive Officer who shall be the ex officio member; and`
  line
  line `(iii) such other officers of the municipality as the State Government may specify to be ex officio`
  line `members of whom one specified officer shall be the Secretary of the Wards Committee:`
  line
  line `Provided that the ex officio members shall have the right to speak and participate in the meetings of`
  line `the Wards Committee but shall not have the right to vote.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson of the Wards Committee shall be elected by the elected members thereof from`
  line `among themselves.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chairperson shall cease to hold office if he ceases to be a member of the Wards Committee.`
  line `Any casual vacancy in the office of the Chairperson shall be filled by election of another Chairperson`
  line `from among the elected members of the Wards Committee as soon as may be after the occurrence of the`
  line vacancy.
  line
  line `(5) The powers and functions of the Wards Committee and the manner of conduct of business at its`
  line `meetings shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (40413)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Reservation of seats.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40413&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) In every municipality, out of the total strength of elected members`
  line `determined under section 15, the State Government shall subject to such rules as may be prescribed, by`
  line `notification, reserve--`
  line
  line `(i) such number of seats to the Scheduled Castes and the Scheduled Tribes as may be determined`
  line `by them, subject to the condition that the number of seats so reserved shall bear, as nearly as may be,`
  line `the same proportion to the total number of seats to be filled by direct election to the Municipal`
  line `Council, as the population of the Scheduled Castes, or as the case may be, of the Scheduled Tribes in`
  line `that municipality bears to the total population of that municipality; and such seats may be allotted by`
  line `rotation to different wards in the municipality;`
  line
  line `(ii) not less than one-third of the total number of seats reserved under sub-section (1) shall be`
  line `reserved for women belonging to the Scheduled Castes or as the case may be, the Scheduled Tribes;`
  line
  line `(iii) not less than one-third (including the number of seats reserved for women belonging to the`
  line `Scheduled Tribes and the Scheduled Castes) of the total number of seats to be filled by direct election`
  line `to every Council, for women; and such seats may be allotted by rotation to different wards in a`
  line municipality.
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section the expressions "Scheduled Castes", "Scheduled Tribes" shall have the`
  line `meanings respectively assigned to them in clauses (24) and (25) of article 366 of the Constitution of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The office of Chairpersons of the municipalities shall be reserved for the Scheduled Castes, the`
  line `Scheduled Tribes and women in such manner as the State Government may prescribe by notification in`
  line `this regard.`
  line
  line `(3) The reservation of seats under sub-section (1) including the reservation of office of Chairperson`
  line `(other than the reservation for women) under sub-section (2) shall cease to have effect on the expiration`
  line `of the period specified in article 334 of the Constitution of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (40414)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Allocation of reserved seats and delimitation of wards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40414&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The State Government shall carry out`
  line `the determination of the boundaries of the wards in a municipality and the allocation of seats reserved in`
  line `favour of the Scheduled Castes, the Scheduled Tribes and women among the wards in the prescribed`
  line manner.
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (40415)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Disqualifications for membership.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40415&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall be disqualified for being chosen as and`
  line `for being, a member of a municipality--`
  line
  line `(a) if he is so disqualified by or under any law for the time being in force for the purposes of`
  line `elections to the Manipur Legislative Assembly:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall be disqualified on the ground that he is less than twenty-five years`
  line `of age, if he has attained the age of twenty-one years;`
  line
  line `(b) if he is so disqualified by or under any law made by Manipur Legislative Assembly;`
  line
  line `(c) if he is not registered as an elector in the electoral roll for a ward;`
  line
  line `(d) if he is not ordinarily resident within the ward from which he is seeking election.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--The expression "ordinarily resident" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in`
  line `section 20 of the Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950).`
  line
  line `(2) If any question arises as to whether a member of a municipality has become subject to any of the`
  line `disqualifications mentioned in sub-section (1) the question shall be referred for the decision of the`
  line `Election Tribunal in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (40416)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Oath of office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40416&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who is elected or appointed as a Councillor of a municipality`
  line `shall, before entering upon his office under this Act, make and subscribe before such authority as may be`
  line `prescribed for the purpose, an oath or affirmation of his allegiance to the Constitution of India in the`
  line `prescribed form.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person, having been elected, or appointed as a Councillor fails to make and subscribe, within`
  line `three months from the date of the first meeting of the municipality the oath or affirmation laid down in`
  line `sub-section (1) shall cease to hold his office and his office shall be deemed to have become vacant.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (40417)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Appointment of administrator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40417&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The State Government shall appoint a person as an`
  line `administrator to exercise the powers and perform the duties and functions of a municipality until a`
  line `municipality is constituted for such area under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the period of such appointment shall not exceed six months:`
  line
  line `Provided further that an administrator appointed under the provisions of the Manipur Municipalities`
  line `Act, 1976 (Manipur Act 26 of 1976 ) on or before the 12th day of October, 1993 shall be deemed to have`
  line `been validly appointed under that Act and the term of such administrator shall cease to have effect on the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (40418)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Duration of municipalities, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40418&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every municipality, unless sooner dissolved under this`
  line `Act, shall continue for five years from the date appointed for its first meeting after a general election at`
  line `which a quorum is present and no longer:`
  line
  line `Provided that a municipality which is functioning immediately before the commencement of this Act`
  line `shall continue till the expiration of its duration, unless sooner dissolved by a resolution passed to that`
  line `effect by the Legislative Assembly of the State of Manipur.`
  line
  line `(2) An election to constitute a municipality shall be completed--`
  line
  line `(a) before the expiry of its duration specified in sub-section (1);`
  line
  line `(b) before the expiration of a period of six months from the date of its dissolution:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the remainder of the period for which the dissolved municipality would have`
  line `continued is less than six months, it shall not be necessary to hold any election under this sub-section for`
  line `constituting the municipality for such period:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the result of election shall be notified.`
  line
  line `(3) A municipality constituted upon the dissolution of a municipality before the expiration of its`
  line `duration shall continue only for the remainder of the period for which the dissolved municipality would`
  line `have continued under sub-section (1) had it not been so dissolved.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (40419)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Every Council to have Chairperson and a Vice-Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40419&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `For every Council, there shall`
  line `be a Chairperson and a Vice-Chairperson.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (40420)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Election of Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40420&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the Councillors at the first`
  line `meeting of the Council to be called at the instance of the Deputy Commissioner after a general election`
  line `shall elect one of them to be the Chairperson in accordance with rules made in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) Such election shall take place within twenty-one days from the date of notification of the result`
  line `under section 22; and in the case of vacancy in the office of the Chairperson on account of any reason`
  line `other than expiry of the term of office of the Chairperson, within twenty-one days from the date of the`
  line `occurrence of the vacancy.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government shall appoint a person to preside over the meeting and for the purpose of`
  line `the business mentioned in sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (40421)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Election of Vice-Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40421&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `The Councillors shall, either at the meeting mentioned in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 24 or at subsequent meeting elect one among themselves other than the`
  line `Chairperson elected under sub-section (1) of section 24 to be the Vice-Chairperson.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (40422)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Chairperson and Vice-Chairperson cease to hold office as such.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40422&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `When a Councillor who`
  line `holds the office of Chairperson or the Vice-Chairperson ceases, for any reason whatsoever to be a`
  line `Councillor, he shall, at the same time, cease to hold office of the Chairperson or the Vice-Chairperson, as`
  line `the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (40423)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Filling up of vacancies and term of office of persons filling up the vacancy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40423&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `If any`
  line `Councillor is by reason of his death, resignation or removal or otherwise, is unable to complete his full`
  line `term of office, the vacancy so caused shall be filled up by election or appointment, as the case may be, of`
  line `a person under the provisions of this Act and the person so elected or appointed shall hold office for the`
  line `unexpired term of his predecessor:`
  line
  line `Provided that no election for filling up a casual vacancy shall be held if the vacancy occurs within a`
  line `period of six months preceding the date on which the term of office of the Councillor expires.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (40424)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Resignation by Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson and Councillor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40424&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson may`
  line `resign his office by writing a letter of resignation addressed to the Vice-Chairperson, who shall forthwith`
  line `deliver the letter to the Executive Officer.`
  line
  line `(2) The Vice-Chairperson or a Councillor may resign his office by writing a letter of resignation`
  line `addressed to the Chairperson, who shall forthwith deliver the letter to the Executive Officer.`
  line
  line `(3) The resignation under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall take effect from the date on which it`
  line `is accepted by the Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The Executive Officer shall forthwith intimate the fact of resignation received under`
  line `sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) to the Council and the State Government.`
  line
  line `(5) On receipt of the intimation under sub-section (4), the State Government shall notify in the`
  line `Official Gazette the fact of the resignation and occurrence of casual vacancy consequent thereon.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (40425)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Removal of Councillors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40425&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may remove any elected Councillor on the`
  line `ground of his misconduct in the discharge of his duties if the removal is recommended by a resolution of`
  line `the municipality passed at a special meeting called for the purpose and supported by a majority of the total number of Councillors of the municipality and by a majority of not less than two-third of`
  line `Councillors present and voting in such a meeting.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may remove any Councillor--`
  line
  line `(a) if he ceases to reside within the municipality continuously for a period of twelve months; or`
  line
  line `(b) if he has been declared by the State Government by notification to have violated his oath or`
  line `affirmation of allegiance; or`
  line
  line `(c) if he becomes disqualified by or under any law for the time being in force for the purposes of`
  line `elections to the Manipur Legislative Assembly; or`
  line
  line `(d) if he has, within the meaning of section 59 knowingly acquired or continued to hold without`
  line `the permission in writing of the State Government, directly or indirectly or as a partner, any share or`
  line `interest in any contract or employment with, by or on behalf, of the municipality; or`
  line
  line `(e) if he is in arrears of any kind of dues to the municipality for more than six months after a bill`
  line `or a notice has been duly served on him:`
  line
  line `Provided that no Councillor shall be removed under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) unless he has`
  line `been given an opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (40426)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Effect of removal of a Councillor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40426&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `No Councillor of a Nagar Panchayat or a Council who has`
  line `been removed from his office under sub-section (1) or under clause (b), (c), (d) or (e) of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 29 shall be eligible for election or re-election as a Councillor for such period as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (40427)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `No-confidence motion against Chairperson or Vice-Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40427&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government`
  line `may remove by a notification in the Official Gazette, from office the Chairperson or the`
  line `Vice-Chairperson, in pursuance of a resolution passed by a majority of the total number of the`
  line `Councillors and supported by not less than two-third of the Councillors present and voting at a meeting`
  line `specially convened for the purpose under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1) a meeting of the Nagar Panchayat or of the Council shall be`
  line `held in the following manner, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the meeting shall be convened by the Executive Officer on a requisition signed by not less than`
  line `one-fifth of the total number of Councillors constituting the Nagar Panchayat or the Council for the`
  line `time being;`
  line
  line `(ii) the notice of such a meeting specifying the time and place thereof shall be despatched by the`
  line `Executive Officer to every Councillor ten days before the meeting;`
  line
  line `(iii) the Chairperson or the Vice-Chairperson, as the case may be, against whom the resolution`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1) is to be moved, shall not preside over the meeting;`
  line
  line `(iv) a copy of the notice shall be sent to the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) If the office of the Chairperson becomes vacant all powers and duties of the Chairperson, may,`
  line `until the election of a new Chairperson be exercised and performed by the Vice-Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(4) The removal of the Chairperson or the Vice-Chairperson under sub-section (1) shall be effective`
  line `from the date of its resolution in this regard.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (40428)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Grant of leave of absence to Chairperson or Vice-Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40428&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Nagar Panchayat or`
  line `the Council, as the case may be, may, from time to time, grant such leave of absence to the Chairperson or`
  line `the Vice-Chairperson as it may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(2) If a Chairperson or a Vice-Chairperson remains absent from office owing to illness or any other`
  line `cause for a period exceeding three months without the leave of the Nagar Panchayat or the Council, as the`
  line `case may be, he shall cease to be Chairperson or Vice-Chairperson, as the case may be, and his office`
  line `shall become vacant.`
  line
  line `(3) During the absence on leave of the Chairperson, the Vice-Chairperson and in the like event in the`
  line `case of a Vice-Chairperson such one of the Councillors as may be elected by them to act as Vice-Chairperson, shall discharge the functions of the Chairperson or the Vice-Chairperson, as the case`
  line `may be.`
  line
  line `(4) The Vice-Chairperson or the Councillor shall, during and in respect of the period in which he is`
  line `acting as, or discharging the function of Chairperson or Vice-Chairperson, as the case may be, exercise`
  line `the powers conferred and perform the duties imposed on a Chairperson or a Vice-Chairperson by or under`
  line `this Act or by any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (40429)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Powers and functions of the Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40429&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the function of the Chairperson--`
  line
  line `(a) to preside, unless prevented by reasonable cause, over all meetings of the Nagar Panchayat or`
  line `the Council, as the case may be, and subject to the provisions of the bye-laws for the time being in`
  line `force, to regulate the conduct of business at such meetings;`
  line
  line `(b) to watch over the financial and executive administration of the Nagar Panchayat or the`
  line `Council, as the case may be, and perform such executive functions as may be allotted to him by or`
  line `under this Act and rules or bye-laws framed thereunder;`
  line
  line `(c) to exercise supervisory and executive control over acts and duties of all officers and`
  line `employees of the Nagar Panchayat or the Council, as the case may be, in matters respecting their`
  line `executive functions and the accounts and records of the Nagar Panchayat or the Council, as the case`
  line `may be;`
  line
  line `(d) to direct, in case of emergency, the execution or stoppage of any work or doing of any act`
  line `which requires the sanction of the Nagar Panchayat or the Council, as the case may be, and the`
  line `immediate execution or doing of which is, in his opinion necessary for the service or safety of the`
  line `public, and the expenses incurred in the execution of such work or doing of such act shall be paid`
  line `from Municipal Fund:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) he shall not act under clause (d) in contravention of any order of the Nagar Panchayat or the`
  line `Council, as the case may be, prohibiting the execution of any particular work or the doing of any`
  line `particular act; and`
  line
  line `(b) he shall report forthwith the action taken under clause (d) and the reasons therefor to the`
  line `Nagar Panchayat or the Council, as the case may be, at its next meeting.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (40430)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Function of Vice-Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40430&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the function of the Vice-Chairperson--`
  line
  line `(a) in the absence of the Chairperson and unless prevented by reasonable cause, to preside over`
  line `the meetings of the Nagar Panchayat or the Council, as the case may be, and he shall, when so`
  line `presiding, exercise the same authority as is vested in the Chairperson under clause (a) of section 33;`
  line
  line `(b) pending the election of a Chairperson, or during the absence of the Chairperson to exercise the`
  line `powers and perform the duties of the Chairperson.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (40431)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Remuneration of Chairperson and Vice-Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40431&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson, the`
  line `Vice-Chairperson or any other Councillor of a Council may be granted by the Council such remuneration`
  line `or such allowance as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the expenditure to be incurred under this section shall without prejudice to the`
  line `provisions of section 71, be paid out of the Municipal Fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (40432)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Powers, authority and responsibilities of municipalities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40432&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government as and`
  line `when it considers expedient may, by notification, entrust--`
  line
  line `(a) the municipalities with the function of--`
  line
  line `(i) the preparation of plans for economic development and social justice;`
  line
  line `(ii) the performance of functions and the implementation of schemes as may be entrusted to`
  line `including those in relation to the matters listed in the Schedule;`
  line
  line `(b) the Committees with such powers and authority as may be necessary to enable them to carry`
  line `out the responsibilities conferred upon them including those in relation to the matters listed in the`
  line Schedule.
  line
  line `(2) On entrustment of functions under sub-section (1), the Government shall allot to the municipality`
  line `such fund and personnel as may be necessary to enable the municipality to discharge the functions and`
  line `duties so entrusted.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (40433)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Obligatory functions of the municipality.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40433&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of every municipality to make`
  line `reasonable provision for the following matters within the municipality under its jurisdiction, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) lighting public roads and places;`
  line
  line `(b) watering public roads and places;`
  line
  line `(c) cleaning public roads, places and sewers and all spaces not being private property, which are`
  line `open to the enjoyment of the public whether such spaces are vested in the municipality or not,`
  line `removing noxious vegetation and abating all public nuisance;`
  line
  line `(d) removing filth, rubbish, night-soil, odour or any other noxious or offensive matter from`
  line `privies, latrines, urinals, cess-pools or other common receptacles or such matter in or pertaining to a`
  line `building or buildings;`
  line
  line `(e) extinguishing fires and protecting life and property when fire occurs;`
  line
  line `(f) regulating offensive or dangerous trades or practices;`
  line
  line `(g) removing obstructions and projections in public roads or places and in spaces not being`
  line `private property, which are open to the enjoyment of the public whether such spaces are vested in the`
  line `municipality or belong to the State Government;`
  line
  line `(h) securing or removing dangerous buildings or places and reclaiming unhealthy localities;`
  line
  line `(i) acquiring, maintaining, changing and regulating places for the disposal of dead bodies and of`
  line `the carcasses of dead animals;`
  line
  line `(j) constructing, altering and maintaining public roads, culverts, municipal boundary marks,`
  line `markets, slaughter-houses, drains, sewers, drainage-works, sewerage-works, baths, washing-places,`
  line `drinking-fountains, tanks, wells, dams and the like;`
  line
  line `(k) constructing public latrines, privies and urinals;`
  line
  line `(l) obtaining a supply or an additional supply of water, proper and sufficient for preventing`
  line `danger to the health of inhabitants from the insufficiency or unwholesomeness of the existing supply;`
  line
  line `(m) naming streets and numbering houses;`
  line
  line `(n) registering births and deaths;`
  line
  line `(o) suitable accommodation for any calves, cows or buffaloes required within the municipality for`
  line `the supply of animal lymph;`
  line
  line `(p) printing such annual reports on the administration of the municipality as may be necessary or`
  line `as the State Government may by general or special orders require the municipality to print;`
  line
  line `(q) making arrangements for preparation of compost manure from night-soil and rubbish; and`
  line
  line `(r) establishing and maintaining cattle ponds.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (40434)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Special duties of municipalities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40434&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `Subject to such reasonable provisions as may be made under`
  line `section 37 every municipality shall make reasonable provision for the following special matters,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) providing special medical aid and accommodation for the sick in times of a dangerous disease`
  line `and taking such measures as may be required to prevent the outbreak or suppress and prevent the`
  line `recurrence of the disease; and`
  line
  line `(b) giving relief and establishing and maintaining relief works, in times of famine or scarcity, to`
  line `or for destitute persons within the limits of the municipality.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (40435)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Discretionary functions of municipality.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40435&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `A municipality may, at its discretion, provide out of`
  line `the municipal property and fund, either wholly or partly, for--`
  line
  line `(a) laying out, whether in areas previously built upon or not, new public roads and acquiring land`
  line `for the purpose, including land acquired for the construction of buildings for curtilages thereof, to`
  line `about on such roads;`
  line
  line `(b) constructing, establishing, maintaining, or contributing to the maintenance of public parks,`
  line `gardens, libraries, museums, reading rooms, halls, offices, dharmashalas, rest-houses, encamping`
  line `grounds and other public buildings and places;`
  line
  line `(c) constructions and maintaining, where necessary suitable sanitary houses for the habitation of`
  line `the poor and granting loans for the construction of such houses or for effecting necessary`
  line `improvements connected therewith;`
  line
  line `(d) providing accommodation for any class of servants employed by the municipality or granting`
  line `loans to such servants for construction of houses subject to the rules made in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(e) planting and maintaining trees in the roadside;`
  line
  line `(f) securing or assisting to secure suitable places for the carrying on the offensive trades`
  line `mentioned in section 167;`
  line
  line `(g) supplying, constructing and maintaining receptacles, fitting pipes, and other appliances`
  line `whatsoever on or for the use of private premises, for receiving and conducting the sewage thereof into`
  line `sewers under the control of the municipality;`
  line
  line `(h) the public health and infant welfare;`
  line
  line `(i) contribution towards any public fund raised for the relief of human suffering within or without`
  line `the municipality;`
  line
  line `(j) any public reception, ceremony, entertainment, or exhibition within the municipality by a`
  line `resolution passed at a general meeting and supported by one-half of the total number of Councillors;`
  line
  line `(k) the organisation or maintenance of shops or stall for the sale of necessities of life;`
  line
  line `(l) holding fairs and exhibitions;`
  line
  line `(m) supply of milk;`
  line
  line `(n) establishing labour welfare centres for its employees and subsidizing the activities of any`
  line `association, union or club of such employees by grant of loan for its general advancement;`
  line
  line `(o) maintenance of ambulance service;`
  line
  line `(p) establishing and maintaining public hospitals and dispensaries and providing public medical`
  line service;
  line
  line `(q) providing facilities for antifrabic treatment and meeting the expenses of indigent person`
  line `undergoing antifrabic treatment within or outside the municipal limits;`
  line
  line `(r) housing and maintaining destitute, orphans and cripples and maintaining maternity centre and`
  line `child welfare clinics;`
  line
  line `(s) establishing rescue homes;`
  line
  line `(t) any other matter which is likely to promote education or the public health safety or`
  line `convenience or the advancement of economic condition of the inhabitants of the municipality or`
  line `which is necessary for the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (40436)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Management of public institution by municipality to vest in it.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40436&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `The management, control and`
  line `administration of every public institution exclusively maintained out of the municipal property and fund`
  line `shall vest in the municipality by which it is so maintained.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (40437)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Appointment of Executive Officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40437&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be an Executive Officer of every Nagar`
  line `Panchayat or Council, as the case may be, who shall also function as Secretary to the Nagar Panchayat or`
  line `Council, as the case may be, and all other officers and employees of the Nagar Panchayat or Council, as`
  line `the case may be, shall be subordinate to him.`
  line
  line `(2) A Nagar Panchayat or Council, as the case may be, shall appoint an Executive Officer with the`
  line `concurrence of the State Government and the State Government may, if any particular Nagar Panchayat`
  line `or Council, as the case may be, does not make such appointment, appoint any person as such officer in`
  line `respect of that Nagar Panchayat or Council, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) A Nagar Panchayat or Council, as the case may be, may in addition to the Executive Officer, also`
  line `appoint other officer to assist the Executive Officer with the concurrence of the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (40438)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Main functions of the Executive Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40438&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `The Executive Officer shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) subject to the general control of the Chairperson, watch over the financial and executive`
  line `administration of the Nagar Panchayat or Council, as the case may be, and perform all the duties and`
  line `exercise all the powers imposed or conferred upon him, by or delegated to him under this Act and`
  line `rules and bye-laws framed thereunder; and`
  line
  line `(b) give effect to the decision taken by the Nagar Panchayat or Council, as the case may be, and`
  line `submit periodical reports, if the Nagar Panchayat or Council, as the case may be, so directs, regarding`
  line `the progress made in respect thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (40439)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Appointment of Health Officer, Revenue Officer and Engineer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40439&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Nagar Panchayat`
  line `or Council, as the case may be, shall have a Health Officer, a Revenue Officer and an Engineer for the`
  line `efficient discharge of its functions and duties.`
  line
  line `(2) The Nagar Panchayat or Council, as the case may be, shall appoint a Health Officer, a Revenue`
  line `Officer and the Engineer with the concurrence of the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (40440)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Power of Nagar Panchayat and Council to determine strength of its employees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40440&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except`
  line `as provided in sections 41 and 43 and subject to the approval of the State Government, a Nagar Panchayat`
  line `or a Council may, by a special resolution determine the category and strength of employees required by it,`
  line `for discharge of its functions and duties.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 71, the expenditure incurred on the establishment`
  line `of Nagar Panchayat or a Council shall be paid out of the Municipal Fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (40441)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Power of Nagar Panchayat and Council to appoint its officers and employees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40441&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `Subject to`
  line `the provisions contained in sections 41 and 43 a Nagar Panchayat or a Council shall have power to`
  line `appoint its officers and employees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairperson may fill up such non-technical posts in the Grades III and IV in such`
  line `manner as may be laid down in bye-laws framed in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (40634)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Disciplinary action against employees of Nagar Panchayat and Council and conditions of their services, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40634&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) An employee of a Nagar Panchayat or a Council who is aggrieved by an order of`
  line `the Chairperson in a disciplinary proceeding against him shall have right to appeal to the Nagar Panchayat`
  line `or the Council within thirty days from the date of service of such order on him.`
  line
  line `(2) An employee who is aggrieved by an order of the Nagar Panchayat or the Council may prefer an`
  line `appeal to the State Government against such an order within sixty days from the date of service of such`
  line `order:`
  line
  line `Provided that no appeal against an order other than an order for removal or dismissal shall lie to the`
  line `State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the disciplinary action, conditions of the service and`
  line `qualifications in respect of the employees of a Nagar Panchayat or a Council shall be the same as`
  line `applicable to the employees of the State Government, from time to time.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (40443)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Gratuity and pension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40443&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `The rules relating to gratuities and pensions applicable to the employees`
  line `of the State Government shall apply to the employees of the Nagar Panchayat or, as the case may be, the`
  line `Council and shall be paid out of the Fund of the Nagar Panchayat or, as the case may be, of the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (40444)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40444&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may make rules regarding the appointment,`
  line `salaries, condition of services, powers, duties and functions of the Executive Officer, other officers and`
  line `employees of the Nagar Panchayat or the Council and other relevant matters connected thereof:`
  line
  line `Provided that no disciplinary action shall be taken against the Executive Officer except with the`
  line `approval of the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (40445)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Meeting of a Nagar Panchayat or of a Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40445&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be at least one meeting of the`
  line `Nagar Panchayat or the Council for transaction of its business in every month to be held on such date as is`
  line `fixed by the Nagar Panchayat or the Council at a special meeting convened for the purpose, at the`
  line `municipal office, if any, or other convenient place of which notice has been duly given.`
  line
  line `(2) If there be no business to be laid before the Nagar Panchayat or the Council at any monthly`
  line `meeting, the Chairperson shall, instead of calling the meeting, give notice of the fact to each Councillor`
  line `three days before the date which is fixed for the monthly meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson, or in his absence the Vice-Chairperson may, on a written requisition of not not`
  line `less than one-half of the total number of Councillors, call a special meeting.`
  line
  line `(4) If the Chairperson or the Vice-Chairperson, as the case may be, fails to call a special meeting`
  line `within fifteen days after any such requisition has been made, the meeting may be called by the`
  line `Councillors who made the requisition.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (40446)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Chairperson of meeting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40446&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `If at a meeting neither the Chairperson nor the Vice-Chairperson is`
  line `present, the Councillors present shall elect one of them to preside over the meeting and such Councillor`
  line `shall perform all the duties and exercise all the powers of the Chairperson of Nagar Panchayat or a`
  line `Council when presiding over a meeting:`
  line
  line `Provided that no candidate for election to the office of the Chairperson or the Vice-Chairperson shall`
  line `preside at such election.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (40447)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Manner of deciding questions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40447&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise expressly provided in or under this Act, all`
  line `questions brought before any meeting of the Nagar Panchayat or of the Council or of any of its`
  line `committees shall be decided by a majority of votes of the Councillors present and voting and in the case`
  line `of equality of votes, on any question the persons presiding shall have a second or casting vote:`
  line
  line `Provided that at the election--`
  line
  line `(a) of Chairperson or Vice-Chairperson; or`
  line
  line `(b) of a Councillor to represent the Nagar Panchayat or the Council, as the case may be, under the`
  line `provisions of any other law for the time being in force,`
  line
  line `in case of equality of votes, the person presiding shall not exercise his casting vote and the result shall be`
  line `decided by lot.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (40448)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Adjournment of meeting in the absence of quorum.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40448&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) No business shall be transacted at a`
  line `meeting unless a quorum of one-third of the total number of Councillors of a Nagar Panchayat, or a`
  line `Council be present:`
  line
  line `Provided that in cases where the total number of Councillors of a Nagar Panchayat or a Council is not`
  line `divisible by three, the total number shall be increase by such minimum number as to make the total`
  line `number divisible by three.`
  line
  line `(2) If there be no quorum present at a meeting the Chairperson or in his absence the`
  line `Vice-Chairperson shall adjourn the meeting to such hour of any future day as he may reasonably fix. A`
  line `notice of such adjournment shall be fixed upon a notice board in the municipal office, and the business`
  line `which would have been brought before the original meeting, has there been a quorum thereat, shall be brought before the adjourned meeting and may be disposed of at such meeting or at any subsequent`
  line `adjournments thereof whether there be a quorum present or not.`
  line
  line `(3) A notice of adjournment exhibited in the notice board of the municipal office on the day on which`
  line `the meeting is adjourned, shall be sufficient notice of the subsequent meeting.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (40449)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Minutes of proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40449&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) Minutes of the proceedings of each meeting of a Nagar Panchayat`
  line `or of a Council or any of its Committee shall be recorded in a book to be kept for the purpose separately`
  line `for the Nagar Panchayat or the Council and for each of its Committees and shall be signed by the persons`
  line `who presided over the meeting.`
  line
  line `(2) The minutes of the meeting of a Nagar Panchayat or of a Council shall at all reasonable times and`
  line `without charge, be open to inspection, by any member of the public.`
  line
  line `(3) The minutes of the proceedings of all meetings of the Nagar Panchayat or of the Council shall`
  line `forthwith be forwarded by the Executive Officer to the Deputy Commissioner, the Director and to the`
  line `State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (40450)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Modification and cancellation of resolution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40450&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `No resolution of a Nagar Panchayat or of a`
  line `Council shall be modified or cancelled except by a resolution supported by not less than two-thirds of the`
  line `total number of Councillors and passed at a meeting whereof notice shall be given setting forth fully the`
  line `proposed resolution to modify or cancel at such meeting and the motion of proposition for modification or`
  line `cancellation of such resolution.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (40628)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Right of Government Officers to attend, address and take part in the meeting of the Nagar Panchayat or of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40628&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `The Deputy Commissioner, the Director and such other officers as the`
  line `State Government may, by general or special order specify in this behalf, shall be entitled to attend any`
  line `meeting of a Nagar Panchayat or of a Council within their jurisdiction, address it on any matter affecting`
  line `the work of their department and take part in the meetings thereof, but shall not have the right to vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (40452)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Appointment of Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40452&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Nagar Panchayat or the Council at a meeting may`
  line `appoint, from time to time, committees to be called "Standing Committee" to assist it in the discharge of`
  line `any specific duties devolved upon it under this Act, within the whole or any portion of the municipality`
  line `and may delegate to any such committee all or any of its powers which may be necessary for the purpose`
  line `of rendering such assistance, or withdraw all or any such powers, so delegated.`
  line
  line `(2) Each Committee shall consist of Councillors and, when necessary, of such residents with special`
  line `qualification when the Nagar Panchayat or the Council at a meeting desires to appoint, in such a case the`
  line `number of Councillors shall not be less than two-thirds of the total number of the members of the`
  line `Committee:`
  line
  line `Provided that no Councillor who has been appointed as a member of one committee, shall be`
  line `appointed as such in another committee at a time.`
  line
  line `(3) The members of such committees shall be liable to all the obligations imposed by this Act on the`
  line `Councillors of the Nagar Panchayat or of the Council in respect of such powers as may be delegated to`
  line them.
  line
  line `(4) All the proceedings of any such committee shall be subject to confirmation by the Nagar`
  line `Panchayat or the Council at a meeting.`
  line
  line `(5) All questions connected with the removal or resignation of members of committee shall be settled`
  line `by the Nagar Panchayat or the Council at a meeting.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (40453)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Chairperson of Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40453&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson of the Nagar Panchayat or of the Council, as`
  line `the case may be, if he is a member of any committee, shall be ex officio, Chairperson, thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) The Vice-Chairperson of the Nagar Panchayat or of the Council, as the case may be, if appointed`
  line `a member of any committee of which the Chairperson is not a member, shall be ex officio Chairperson`
  line thereof.
  line
  line `(3) When neither the Chairperson nor the Vice-Chairperson of Nagar Panchayat or of a Council, as`
  line `the case may be, is a member of a committee, the Chairperson of such committee shall be nominated by`
  line `the Chairperson of the Nagar Panchayat or of the Council, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (40454)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Liability for loss, waste or misapplication of funds and property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40454&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `Every Chairperson,`
  line `Vice-Chairperson, Councillor, officer or employees of a Nagar Panchayat or of a Council including a`
  line `Government servant whose services are lent to the Nagar Panchayat or to the Council, shall be liable for`
  line `the loss, waste or misapplication of any money or other property owned by or vested in the Nagar`
  line `Panchayat or the Council, if such loss, waste or misapplication is a direct consequence of any illegal act,`
  line `omission, neglect or misconduct on his part; and a suit for compensation may be instituted against him in`
  line `any Court of competent jurisdiction by the Nagar Panchayat or by the Council, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (40455)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Disqualifications of Councillors having share or interest in contract.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40455&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `No Councillor of a`
  line `Nagar Panchayat or of a Council shall have without the written permission of the State Government,`
  line `directly or indirectly, any share or interest in any contract, lease, sale or purchase of land or any`
  line `agreement for the same or any kind whatsoever to which the Nagar Panchayat or Council is a party, or`
  line `shall hold any office of profit under it, and if any Councillor shall have such share or interest or shall hold`
  line `such office he shall thereby become disqualified to continue in office as a Councillor:`
  line
  line `Provided that a Councillor shall not be so disqualified or liable by reason--`
  line
  line `(a) of having a share or interest in--`
  line
  line `(i) a contract entered into between the Nagar Panchayat or the Council, as the case may be,`
  line `and any incorporated or registered company or any registered Co-operative Society of which such`
  line `Councillor is a member or shareholder; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any agreement for the loan of money, or any security for the payment of money only; or`
  line
  line `(iii) any newspaper in which any advertisement relating to the affairs of the municipality is`
  line `inserted; or`
  line
  line `(b) of his being professionally engaged on behalf of the Nagar Panchayat or the Council, as the`
  line `case may be, as a legal or medical practitioner and receiving a fee for services rendered in his`
  line `professional capacity.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (40629)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Penalty in case Councillors, executive officer, etc., having interest in a contract, etc., with the Nagar Panchayat or Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40629&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `In a Nagar Panchayat or in a Council--`
  line
  line `(a) subject to the proviso to section 59 any Councillor who acquires, directly or indirectly any`
  line `share or interest in any contract or employment with, under, by or on behalf of a Nagar Panchayat or a`
  line `Council of which he is a Councillor;`
  line
  line `(b) any executive officer or employee who acquires directly or indirectly any share or interest in`
  line `any contract with, under, by or on behalf of a Nagar Panchayat or a Council except in so far as it`
  line `relates to his own employment as executive officer or an employee, shall be punishable with fine`
  line `which may extend to five thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (40457)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Disqualification from voting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40457&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `No Councillor of a Nagar Panchayat or of a Council or no`
  line `member of a committee shall vote or take part in the discussion of any question at a meeting of the Nagar`
  line `Panchayat or of a Council or committee if the question is one in which he has direct or indirect pecuniary`
  line interest.
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (40458)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Municipal property and vesting thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40458&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) All property within the municipality, other than`
  line `private property or property maintained by the Government or other local authority, shall vest in the`
  line `Nagar Panchayat or the Council, as the case may be, and shall, with all other property of whatever nature`
  line `and kind which may become vested in the Nagar Panchayat or the Council, as the case may be, be under`
  line `its direction, management and control, unless the State Government otherwise directs by notification,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) all public roads including the soil, the pavements, stones and other materials thereof, and all`
  line `drains, bridges, trees, erections, materials, implements and other things provided for such roads;`
  line
  line `(b) all public streams, channels, water courses, springs, tanks, reservoirs, cisterns, wells,`
  line `aqueducts, conduits, tunnels, pipes, pumps and other water-works, whether made, laid or created at the cost of the Nagar Panchayat or of the Council or otherwise and all bridges, buildings, engines,`
  line `works, materials and things connected therewith or appertaining thereto and also any adjacent land,`
  line `not being private property, appertaining to any public tanks:`
  line
  line `Provided that water-pipes and water-works connected therewith or appertaining thereto which`
  line `with the consent of the Nagar Panchayat or of the Council are laid or set up in any street by the`
  line `owners of any mill, factory, workshop or the like primarily for the use of their employees shall not be`
  line `deemed to be public water-works by reason of their use by the public;`
  line
  line `(c) all public sewers and drains, and all works, materials and things appertaining thereto and other`
  line `conservancy works;`
  line
  line `(d) all sewage, rubbish and offensive matter collected by the Nagar Panchayat or by the Council`
  line `from roads, latrines, sewers, cesspools and other places;`
  line
  line `(e) all public lamps, lamp-posts and apparatus connected there with or appertaining thereto, and`
  line `all public gates, markets, slaughter houses and public buildings of every description which have been`
  line `constructed or are maintained out of the municipal fund; and`
  line
  line `(f) all land or other property transferred to the Nagar Panchayat or Council, as the case may be, by`
  line `the Government or acquired by the Nagar Panchayat or Council, as the case may be, by gift, purchase`
  line `or otherwise for local public purposes.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may, by notification direct that any property which has vested in the Nagar`
  line `Panchayat or the Council, as the case may be, shall cease to be so vested, and the State Government may`
  line `pass such orders as it may deem fit regarding the disposal and management of such property.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government may resume any immovable property transferred to the Nagar Panchayat or`
  line `the Council, as the case may be, by itself or any other local authority for a public purpose on payment of`
  line `the amount paid by the Nagar Panchayat or by the Council, as the case may be, for such transfer and the`
  line `market value at the date of resumption of any building or works subsequently created or executed thereon`
  line `by the Nagar Panchayat or by the Council, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that compensation need not be paid for buildings or works constructed or created in`
  line `contravention of the terms of the transfer.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (40459)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Transfer of municipal property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40459&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 6 or 13, no`
  line `Nagar Panchayat or the Council, as the case may be, shall transfer any immovable property except in`
  line `pursuance of a resolution passed at a meeting thereof by a majority of not less than two-third of its`
  line `members and except when it is not required for local public purposes:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of property which has been transferred to it by the State Government the`
  line `transfer under this section shall be subject to the previous sanction of the State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing in this section shall apply to leases of immovable property for a term not`
  line `exceeding two years in total.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (40460)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Execution of contracts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40460&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Nagar Panchayat or the Council, as the case may be, may enter`
  line `into any contract necessary for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every contract made by or on behalf of the Nagar Panchayat or the Council, as the case may be, in`
  line `respect of any sum exceeding ten thousand rupees shall be sanctioned by the Nagar Panchayat or the`
  line `Council, as the case may be, at a meeting and shall be in writing and shall be signed by at least two`
  line `Councillors one of whom shall be the Chairperson or the Vice-Chairperson and in absence of both the`
  line `Executive Officer. Every such contract shall be sealed with common seal of the Nagar Panchayat or the`
  line `Council, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) Any contract made in contravention of sub-section (2) shall not be binding on the Nagar`
  line `Panchayat or the Council, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (40461)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Transfer of private roads, etc., to Nagar Panchayat or Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40461&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Nagar Panchayat or`
  line `the Council at a meeting may agree with the person in whom the properly in any road, bridge, tank, ghat,`
  line `well, channel, or drain, vests to take over the property therein or the control thereof, and after`
  line `such agreement may declare by notice in writing put up thereon or near thereto that such roads, bridge,`
  line `tank, ghat, well, channel or drain has been transferred to the Nagar Panchayat or the Council, as the case`
  line `may be.`
  line
  line `(2) On completion of the transfer, the property shall vest in the Nagar Panchayat or the Council, as`
  line `the case may be, and shall thenceforth be repaired and maintained out of the municipal fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (40462)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Acquisition of land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40462&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `When any land, whether within or without the limits of a municipality is`
  line `required for the purposes of this Act, the State Government may, at the request of the Nagar Panchayat or`
  line `the Council, proceed to acquire it under the provisions of the Land Acquisition Act, 1894 (1 of 1894), and`
  line `on payment by the Nagar Panchayat or the Council, as the case may be, of the compensation awarded`
  line `under that Act and of any other charges incurred in acquiring the land, the land shall vest in the Nagar`
  line `Panchayat or the Council, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (40463)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Formation and custody for municipal fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40463&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be formed for each Nagar`
  line `Panchayat and for each Council a municipal fund to be called the "Municipal Fund" and it shall be held`
  line `by the Nagar Panchayat or by the Council, as the case may be, for the purposes of this Act and subject to`
  line `the provisions thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) The Municipal Fund shall vest in the Nagar Panchayat or the Council, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (40464)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Credit of moneys to the municipal fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40464&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be credited to the municipal fund:--`
  line
  line `(a) all sums received by or on behalf of the Nagar Panchayat or the Council under the provisions`
  line `of this Act or of any other law for the time being in force or under any contract;`
  line
  line `(b) the balance, if any, standing at the credit of the Nagar Panchayat or the Council at the`
  line `commencement of this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) all proceeds of the disposal of property by, or on behalf of, the Nagar Panchayat or the`
  line Council;
  line
  line `(d) all rents accruing from any property of the Nagar Panchayat or the Council;`
  line
  line `(e) all moneys raised by any tax levied for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) all fees payable and levied under this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) all moneys received by the Nagar Panchayat or by the Council by way of compensation or for`
  line `compounding offences under the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) all moneys received by, or on behalf of, the Nagar Panchayat or the Council from the State`
  line `Government or private individuals by way of grants, contribution, gift or deposits; and`
  line
  line `(i) all interest and profit, arising from any investment of, or from any transaction in connection`
  line `with, any money belonging to the Nagar Panchayat or the Council.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in this section or in this Act shall affect any obligation of a Nagar Panchayat or of a`
  line `Council arising from a trust legally imposed upon or accepted by the Nagar Panchayat or by the Council,`
  line `as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (40465)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Powers of the Nagar Panchayat or of the Council to borrow money.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40465&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Nagar Panchayat`
  line `or a Council may, with the previous sanction of the State Government and subject to such conditions as`
  line `may be prescribed as to security, the rate of interest and the repayment of principal and interest, borrow`
  line `either from the State Government or any financial institution, any sum of money required or empowered`
  line `to undertake under the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) or the rules made thereunder shall apply to grants or loans or`
  line `advance made to a Nagar Panchayat or to a Council by any department, office or authority of the State`
  line `Government or by any local authority or by any other institution towards, and for the purpose of, the`
  line `implementation, achievement and accomplishment of community development schemes and a Nagar`
  line `Panchayat or a Council may accept any such grant or loan which shall be regulated and governed by the`
  line `terms on which, and the conditions subject to which, the same is made or advanced.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (40466)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Application of municipal property and fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40466&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `(1) All property vested in a Nagar Panchayat or`
  line `in a Council under this Act, all funds received by it in accordance with the provisions of this Act and all sums accruing to under the provisions of any law for the time being in force shall, subject to the`
  line `provisions of this Act, be applied for the purposes of this Act, within the limits of the municipality.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), it shall be lawful for a Nagar Panchayat or`
  line `a Council, as the case may be, subject to rules made under this Act:--`
  line
  line `(a) to incur expenditure beyond the municipal limits on the acquisition of land, or on the`
  line `construction, maintenance or repair of works, for the purpose of obtaining supply of water required`
  line `for inhabitants of the municipality or on establishing slaughter houses or places for the disposal of`
  line `night-soil or sewage or carcasses of animals or for drainage works, or for the purpose of providing`
  line `mechanically propelled transport facilities for the conveyance of the public or for the purpose of`
  line `setting up dairies or farms for the supply, distribution and procuring of milk-products for the benefit`
  line `of the inhabitants of the municipality or for any other purpose calculated to promote the health, safety`
  line `or convenience of the inhabitants of the municipality; or`
  line
  line `(b) to take a contribution towards expenditure incurred by any other local authority or out of any`
  line `public fund for measures affecting the health, safety or convenience of public calculated to benefit the`
  line `residents within the limits of the contributing municipality; or`
  line
  line `(c) to create scholarship tenable outside the limits of municipality; or`
  line
  line `(d) to utilise the municipal fire brigade and other mechanical appliance beyond the municipal`
  line `limits; or`
  line
  line `(e) to make with the previous sanction of the State Government any other kind of contribution as`
  line `may be deemed necessary by the Nagar Panchayat or the Council:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section or in any other provision of this Act shall be deemed to make it`
  line `unlawful for a Nagar Panchayat or a Council, when it has constructed works beyond the limits of the`
  line `municipality for the supply of water or electrical energy or for drainage as aforesaid--`
  line
  line `(a) to supply or extend to or for the benefit of any person or building or lands in any place`
  line `whether such place is not within the limits of the said municipality, any quantity of water or electrical`
  line `energy not required for the purpose of this Act within the said municipality or the advantages`
  line `afforded by the system of drainage works, on such terms and conditions with regard to payment and`
  line `to the continuance or such supply advantages as shall be settled by agreement between the Nagar`
  line `Panchayat or the Council, as the case may be, and such persons or the occupier or owner of such`
  line `buildings or land; or`
  line
  line `(b) to incur any expenditure on such terms with regard to payment as may be settled as aforesaid`
  line `for the construction, maintenance, repair or charge of any connection pipe or any electric supply lines`
  line `or other works necessary for the purposes of such supply or for the extension of such supply or for the`
  line `extension of such advantages.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (40467)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title Budget.
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40467&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Nagar Panchayat or a Council at a meeting specially convened for the purpose,`
  line `two months before the close of the financial year, shall prepare in such form and manner as may be`
  line `prescribed, a budget showing inter alia the probable receipts and expenditure during the ensuing year and`
  line `after such revision as may appear requisite it shall pass the budget and such budget shall be submitted to`
  line `the Director for obtaining approval of the State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the approval is not intimated within one month from the date of the receipt of the`
  line `budget by the State Government or the receipt of such other information as is called for by the State`
  line `Government, it shall be taken that the budget is approved.`
  line
  line `(2) The Nagar Panchayat or the Council may, from time to time, revise any estimates of expenditure`
  line `with the view of providing for any modification which it may deem advisable to make in the`
  line `appropriation of the amount at its disposal and such revised budget shall be passed in the manner`
  line `provided in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) When the budget has been passed, the Nagar Panchayat or the Council shall not incur any`
  line `expenditure under any of the heads of the budget in excess of the amount sanctioned under that head`
  line `without making a provision for such excess by a revision of the budget in the manner specified in`
  line `sub-section (2).`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (40468)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40468&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every municipality shall maintain such accounts for every financial`
  line `year in such forms as may be prescribed and submit such statement to the Deputy Commissioner, the`
  line `Director and the State Government and such accounts shall be audited by the Director, Local Fund Audit`
  line `and Accounts of the Government of Manipur in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The municipality shall comply with such directions as the State Government may deem fit to issue`
  line `after going through the audit report respecting it.`
  line
  line `(3) The municipality shall pay out of the municipal fund such sum as may be determined by the State`
  line `Government by way of charges for such audit.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (40469)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Finance Commission for municipalities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40469&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Finance Commission constituted under`
  line `section 97 of the Manipur Panchayati Raj Act, 1994 (26 of 1994), shall also review the financial position`
  line `of the municipalities and make recommendations to the Governor as to--`
  line
  line `(a) the principles which should govern--`
  line
  line `(i) the distribution between the State and the municipalities of the net proceeds of the taxes,`
  line `duties, tolls and fees leviable by the State, which may be divided between them under this Act`
  line `and the allocation between the municipalities at all levels of their respective shares of such`
  line proceeds;
  line
  line `(ii) the determination of the taxes, duties, tolls and fees which may be assigned to, or`
  line `appropriated by, the municipalities;`
  line
  line `(iii) the grant-in-aid to the municipalities from the Consolidated Fund of the State;`
  line
  line `(b) the measures needed to improve the financial position of the municipalities;`
  line
  line `(c) any other matter referred to the Finance Commission by the Governor in the interests of sound`
  line `finance of the municipalities.`
  line
  line `(2) The Governor shall cause every recommendation made by the Commission under this section`
  line `together with an explanatory memorandum as to the action taken thereon to be laid before the Legislature`
  line `of the State.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (40470)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Power to impose taxes by and the funds of the municipalities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40470&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may,`
  line `from time to time, by notification in the Official Gazette--`
  line
  line `(a) authorize a municipality to levy, collect and appropriate such taxes, duties, tolls and fees in`
  line `accordance with such procedure and subject to such limits to be prescribed by it;`
  line
  line `(b) assign to a municipality such taxes, duties, tolls and fees levied and collected by the State`
  line `Government for such purposes and subject to such conditions and limits to be prescribed by it;`
  line
  line `(c) provide for making such grant-in-aid to the municipalities from the Consolidated Fund of the`
  line State.
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (40471)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Taxes which may be imposed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40471&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Chapter and with the`
  line `previous approval of the State Government, municipality may, from time to time, impose in the whole or`
  line `in any part of the municipality any of the following taxes and tolls, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a tax on holding situated within the municipality assessed on their annual value, payable by`
  line `the owner of the building or land or both;`
  line
  line `(b) a tax on all or any of the vehicles, other than covered by the Motor Vehicles Act, 1988`
  line `(59 of 1988), or animals used for riding, driving, draught or burden and used within the limits of the`
  line `municipality whether they are actually kept within or outside the said limits;`
  line
  line `(c) an octroi on goods brought within the limits of the municipality for sale, consumption or use`
  line `within such limits;`
  line
  line `(d) a latrine-tax payable by the owners or occupiers for collections, removal and disposal of`
  line `excrement or offensive matter from latrines, privies, urinals, cess-pools or compounds by the`
  line `municipality, within the limits of the municipality;`
  line
  line `(e) a scavenging-tax;`
  line
  line `(f) lighting-tax where the lighting arrangement is made by the municipality;`
  line
  line `(g) a drainage tax where a system of drainage has been introduced by the municipality;`
  line
  line `(h) a tax on deeds of transfer of immovable property situated within the limits of the municipality;`
  line
  line `(i) a tax on advertisements made within the limits of the municipality other than non-commercial`
  line `undertaking advertisements published in newspapers;`
  line
  line `(j) a water-tax where water is supplied by the municipality;`
  line
  line `(k) market fees on person exposing goods for sale in any market or any place belonging to or`
  line `under the control of the State Government or of the municipality;`
  line
  line `(l) a betterment charge on properties the value of which may be increased as a result of town`
  line `planning scheme implemented by the municipality; and`
  line
  line `(m) any other tax, toll, rate, charge or fee.`
  line
  line `(2) With the previous sanction of the State Government a municipality may, from time to time, charge`
  line `a fee in respect of the issue and renewal of any licence which may be granted by the municipality under`
  line `this Act and in respect of which no fee is leviable under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of any law that may be made by Parliament, any tax or fee which`
  line `immediately before the commencement of this Act, was being lawfully levied under the Manipur`
  line `Municipalities Act, 1976 (Manipur Act 26 of 1976) notwithstanding that such tax or fee is not specified in`
  line `sub-section (1) shall continue to be levied by the Nagar Panchayat or, as the case may be, by the Council.`
  line
  line `(4) The State Government may from time to time direct the municipality to impose any tax or to`
  line `modify the rate of any tax already imposed.`
  line
  line `(5) On default of the municipality to comply with the decision under sub-section (4) within three`
  line `months from the receipt of the direction the municipality may be required to furnish reason as to why the`
  line `tax should not be imposed or modified, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (40472)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Tax on Government holdings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40472&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding any provisions to the contrary all municipal`
  line `taxes including services charges except under clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 75 in respect of`
  line `Government holdings shall be payable to municipality by the Government Department which is in control`
  line `and management of the holdings.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (40473)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Restriction regarding tax on holding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40473&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `The State Government shall have the power to exempt`
  line `by an order published in the Official Gazette any class of building or holding from levying any tax under`
  line `section 75 of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (40474)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Collection of taxes are subject to bye-law, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40474&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `All the taxes mentioned in section 75 shall be`
  line `collected in the manner provided in the bye-laws.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (40475)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Nagar Panchayat or Council to determine the valuation of holding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40475&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `When it has been`
  line `decided to impose any tax on the annual value of holdings, the assessor after making such enquiries as`
  line `may be necessary, shall determine the valuation of all holdings within the municipality as hereinafter`
  line `provided, and shall enter the same in a list called the valuation list, which shall be in the prescribed form:`
  line
  line `Provided that valuation other than general valuation may be made by the municipality through such`
  line `person as may be authorised by the municipality in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (40476)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Returns required for ascertaining annual value.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40476&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `The assessor, in order to prepare the`
  line `valuation list, may whenever he thinks fit, by notice require the owners or occupiers of all holdings to`
  line `furnish him, within fifteen days with returns of the rent or annual value thereof and a description of the`
  line `holdings in such detail as the municipality may direct; and the assessor, at any time between sunrise and`
  line `sunset may enter, inspect and measure any such holdings:`
  line
  line `Provided that at least forty-eight hours, previous notice of the intention to enter, inspect and measure`
  line `any holding shall be given to the owner or occupier thereof, unless he waives his right to such notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (40477)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Penalty for default in furnishing return and for obstruction of assessor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40477&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever`
  line `refuses or fails to furnish any such return for the period of fifteen days from the day on which he has been`
  line `required to do so, or knowingly furnishes a false or incorrect return or description shall be punishable`
  line `with fine not exceeding five hundred rupees and with further fine not exceeding fifty rupees for each day`
  line `during which he omits to furnish a true and correct return.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever obstructs, hinders or prevents the assessor appointed by the municipality from entering`
  line `or inspection or measuring any such holding shall be punishable with fine not exceeding two thousand`
  line rupees.
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (40478)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Determination of annual value of holdings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40478&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `"Annual value" means--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of hotels, colleges, schools, hospitals, factories and such other buildings, a`
  line `proportion not exceeding five per centum, to be fixed by rule made in this behalf of the sum obtained`
  line `by adding the estimated present cost of erecting the building, less depreciation at the rate to be fixed`
  line `by rule to the estimated value of the land appurtenant thereto, and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a building or land not falling within the provisions of clause (a), the gross`
  line `annual rent for which such buildings, exclusive of furniture or machinery therein or such land is`
  line `actually let, or where the building or land is not let or in the opinion of the municipality is let for a`
  line `sum less than its fair letting value, might reasonably be expected to let from year to year:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the annual value of any building would, by reason of exceptional`
  line `circumstances, in the opinion of the municipality be excessive if calculated in the aforesaid manner,`
  line `the municipality may fix the annual value at any less amount which appears to it suitable:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the rules framed in this behalf shall be subject to the prior approval of the`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (40479)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Determination of rate of tax on holding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40479&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `The mode of procedure and system of tax on the land`
  line `and holdings will be such as may be prescribed by the rules to be framed by Government from time to`
  line `time in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (40480)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Preparation of assessment register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40480&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `As soon as possible after the percentage at which the tax`
  line `is to be levied shall have been determined under section 83, the municipality shall cause to be prepared an`
  line `assessment register which shall contain the following particulars, and any other matters which the`
  line `municipality may think proper to include--`
  line
  line `(a) number of the holding on the register with the name of the road, if any, in which the holding is`
  line situated;
  line
  line `(b) annual value of the holding (as stated in the valuation list);`
  line
  line `(c) names of owner and occupier;`
  line
  line `(d) amount of tax payable for the financial year;`
  line
  line `(e) amount of taxes payable separately under clause (a), (d), (f) or (j) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 75;`
  line
  line `(f) amounts of quarterly instalments; and`
  line
  line `(g) if the holding is exempted from assessment, a note to that effect.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (40481)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Powers to assess consolidated tax for building and land on which it stands.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40481&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any`
  line `building belongs to one owner and the land on which it stands and any adjacent land which is usually`
  line `occupied therewith belongs to another the municipality may value such building and land together and`
  line `may impose thereon one consolidated tax.`
  line
  line `(2) The total amount of the tax shall be payable by the owners of the building, who shall thereafter be`
  line `entitled to deduct from the rent which he pays for the land such proportion of the tax so paid by him as is`
  line `equal to the proportion which such rent bears to the annual value of the holdings.`
  line
  line `(3) In case of disputes, the municipality shall determine what amount the owner of the building and of`
  line `the land shall pay respectively.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (40633)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `Reduction of valuation, revision of valuation and assessment and revision of valuation list and assessment register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40633&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `(1) The municipality may, at any time, direct an alteration in, or amendment`
  line `of the assessment register--`
  line
  line `(a) by entering therein the name of any person or any property which in its opinion ought to have`
  line `been entered, or any property which has become liable to taxation after the preparation of the`
  line `assessment register, or`
  line
  line `(b) by substituting therein with effect from the date of succession or transfer, as the case may be,`
  line `for the name of the owner of any holding the name of any other person who has succeeded by transfer`
  line `or otherwise, to the ownership of the holding, or`
  line
  line `(c) by altering the valuation of or assessment on any holding which in its opinion has been`
  line `incorrectly valued or assessed, or`
  line
  line `(d) by re-valuing or re-assessing any holding the value of which has been increased by additions`
  line `or alterations to buildings, or`
  line
  line `(e) by reducing, upon the application of the owner the valuation of any holding which has been`
  line `wholly or partly demolished or destroyed, or the value of which has diminished from any cause`
  line `beyond the control of the owner, or`
  line
  line `(f) by correcting any clerical or arithmetical error.`
  line
  line `(2) The municipality shall give at least one month's notice to any person interested in any alteration`
  line `which the municipality proposes to make under clause (a), (b), (c) or (d) of sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) Every alteration made under sub-section (1) in the assessment register shall be signed by the`
  line `Chairperson or the Vice-Chairperson.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (40483)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Notice to be given to Chairperson of transfers of title of persons liable of payment of tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40483&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever the title to any holding is transferred both the transferor and the transferee shall for the`
  line `purpose of clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 86 within three months after the execution of the`
  line `instrument of transfer, or if no such instrument is executed, within three months after the transfer is`
  line `effected, give notice in writing of such transfer to the municipality.`
  line
  line `(2) in the event of the death of the person in whom such title vests, the person to whom as heir or`
  line `otherwise, the title of the deceased is transferred by descent or demise, shall within one year, from the`
  line `death of the deceased, give notice in writing of such succession to the municipality.`
  line
  line `(3) Every person liable for the payment of taxes on any holding, who transfers his title to or over such`
  line `property, without giving notice of such transfer to the municipality, as aforesaid, shall unless the`
  line `municipality on the ground of hardship arising out of special circumstances, otherwise directs, continue to`
  line `be liable for the payment of all such taxes from time to time payable in respect of the said property until`
  line `he gives such notice, or until the transfer shall have been recorded in the municipal books.`
  line
  line `(4) The municipality may levy a fee not exceeding one hundred rupees for every such transfer of title`
  line `to a holding in addition to the tax provided for in clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 75.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (40484)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `Revisions of valuation list.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40484&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `(1) A new valuation list shall, unless otherwise ordered by the State`
  line `Government, be prepared in the same manner as the original list, once in every five years.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to any alteration or amendment made under section 86 and to the result of any application`
  line `made under section 95 every valuation list or the assessment register shall be valid from the date on which`
  line `the list or register takes effect in the municipality.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (40485)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 89
  title `Appointment of assessor and power of State Government to direct the appointment of assessor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40485&sectionno=89&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `(1) The municipality, for the purpose of general valuation may, with the concurrence of the`
  line `Government, appoint an assessor who shall neither be an employee nor a Councillor of the municipality`
  line `on such pay and with such establishment as it may determine.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 88 if at any time it appears to the State`
  line `Government that the valuation in any municipality is insufficient, excessive or inequitable, the State`
  line `Government may, by an order in writing, require the municipality to revise the valuation or to show cause`
  line `against revision within a specified time, and if the municipality fails to comply with the order or in the`
  line `opinion of the Government the cause shown is inadequate, the State Government may by an order in`
  line `writing require the municipality to appoint with the approval of the State Government an assessor for the`
  line `municipality within a time and for a period to be specified in the order. The order shall fix the pay of the`
  line `assessor and the cost of his establishment, and the pay and cost shall be paid monthly by the municipality.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (40486)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Revision of assessment register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40486&sectionno=90&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `Whenever the valuation list is revised or altered wholly or in`
  line `part or a new percentage is fixed under section 83 the assessment register also shall be revised and all`
  line `consequential changes, made therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (40487)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 91
  title `Effect of revision of assessment register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40487&sectionno=91&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `The first assessment register prepared for any`
  line `municipality under the Act and any revision thereof or alteration therein made under the foregoing section`
  line `shall subject to the provision of sections 86 and 96 take effect, from the beginning of the quarter`
  line `following the publication of the notice mentioned in sections 96.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (40488)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 92
  title `Exemptions and remission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40488&sectionno=92&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `(1) The taxes mentioned in clauses (a), (g) and (l) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 75 shall not be assessed or levied on any building which is used exclusively as a`
  line `place of public worship, or on any holding which is duly registered as a public burial or burning ground`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The municipality may exempt from assessment of the tax mentioned in clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 75 on any holding used for the purpose of a public charity.`
  line
  line `(3) The municipality may reduce the amount payable on account of any of the taxes mentioned in`
  line `clauses (a), (b), (f) and (i) of sub-section (1) of section 75 or remit the same on the ground of excessive`
  line `hardship to the person liable to pay the same:`
  line
  line `Provided that such reduction or remission shall not, unless renewed by the municipality, have effect`
  line `for more than one financial year.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (40489)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 93
  title `Power of assessor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40489&sectionno=93&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `An assessor appointed by the municipality under section 89 shall exercise`
  line `all such powers of valuation as may be vested in him by the municipality or as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (40490)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 94
  title `Publication of notice of assessment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40490&sectionno=94&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the valuation list mentioned in section 79 and`
  line `the assessment register mentioned in section 84 shall have been prepared or revised the Chairperson shall`
  line `sign the same and shall cause them to be deposited in the office of the Nagar Panchayat or as the case`
  line `may be, of the Council, and shall cause a notice to be published in such form and manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(2) In all cases in which any property is for the first time assessed or the assessment is increased, the`
  line `Executive Officer shall also give notice thereof to the owner or occupier of the property.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (40491)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 95
  title `Application for review.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40491&sectionno=95&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who is dissatisfied with the amount assessed upon him`
  line `or with the valuation or assessment of any holding or who disputes his occupation of any holding or his`
  line `liability to be assessed, may apply to the municipality to review the amount of assessment of valuation or`
  line `to exempt him from the assessment of tax:`
  line
  line `Provided that no application shall be entertained unless the applicant has paid all arrears of dues to the`
  line `municipality accorded up to the date of such application other than the sum which has been enhanced by`
  line `the valuation or assessment against which the review application has been filed.`
  line
  line `(2) When an assessor has been appointed under section 89 notice of every such application shall be`
  line `given by the municipality to the assessor.`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (40492)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 96
  title `Procedure for review.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40492&sectionno=96&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every application presented under section 95 shall be heard and`
  line `determined by a Committee consisting of not more than five members.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson or the Vice-Chairperson shall be one of the members of such committee`
  line `ex officio, and the other members shall be appointed from among the Councillors by the Nagar Panchayat`
  line `or, as the case may be, by the Council:`
  line
  line `Provided that no member so appointed shall take part in hearing or determining any application from`
  line `the ward in which he resides, or in the case of an elected member the ward which he represents, but`
  line `nothing in this proviso, shall prevent any such member from giving evidence with regard to the matter`
  line `under enquiry.`
  line
  line `(3) No such application shall be heard or determined by the committee unless at least three members`
  line `including the Chairperson or the Vice-Chairperson are present.`
  line
  line `(4) The committee shall give notice to the applicant of the time and place at which application shall`
  line `be heard, and after taking such evidence and making such enquiries as may be deemed necessary in the`
  line `presence of the objector or his agent, if he appears the committee shall pass such orders as it may deem fit`
  line `in respect of such application.`
  line
  line `(5) If the committee orders that any valuation to which the application relates shall be reduced, brief`
  line `reasons for such reduction shall be recorded.`
  line
  line `(6) The decision of the committee or of a majority of the members thereof, in respect of any`
  line `application referred to in this section shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (40493)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 97
  title `Limitation of time for application for review.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40493&sectionno=97&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `Unless good cause shall be shown to the`
  line `satisfaction of the committee referred to in section 96 for extending the time allowed, and save as is`
  line `otherwise expressly provided in this Act, no such application shall be received after the expiry of one`
  line `month from the date of publication of the notice required by section 94 relating to the list or register`
  line `containing the assessment, in respect of which the application is made, or after the expiry of fifteen days`
  line `from the date of service of the first notice of demand for payment at the rate in respect of which the`
  line `application is made whichever period shall last expire:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if the municipality has served a notice under section 94 on any person, no such`
  line `application shall be received from him after the expiry of fifteen days from the date of such service.`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (40494)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 98
  title `Assessment to be questioned only under Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40494&sectionno=98&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `No objection shall be taken to any assessment`
  line `or valuation in any other manner than is provided in this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (40495)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 99
  title `Tax not invalid for want of form.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40495&sectionno=99&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `No assessment of tax on property and no charge or demand`
  line `of any tax made under authority of this Act shall be invalid for error, defect in form, and it shall be`
  line `enough in any valuation or assessment for purpose if the property so valued or assessed is so described as`
  line `to be generally known and it shall not be necessary to name the owner or occupier thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (40496)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 100
  title `Procedure for imposing taxes, recovery of claims, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40496&sectionno=100&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `The various procedure that may be`
  line `prescribed by the Government from time to time will be followed for imposing and recovery of tax, tolls,`
  line `fees and rates under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (40497)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 101
  title `Recovery from occupier of tax due from non-resident.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40497&sectionno=101&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `If any tax payable under this Act by`
  line `the owner of any holding remains unpaid after the notice of demand has been duly served, and if such`
  line `owner is not resident within the municipality, or the place of abode of such owner is unknown, the tax`
  line `may be recovered from the occupier for the time being of such holding, who may deduct, from the next`
  line `and following payments of his rent the amount which may be so paid by or recovered from him:`
  line
  line `Provided that if any such holding is occupied by more than one person, the sum to be recovered from`
  line `any one of such persons shall be proportionate to the value of the part of the holding in the respective`
  line `occupation of such persons`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (40498)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 102
  title `Recovery from owner of occupier's tax in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40498&sectionno=102&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `If any holding is occupied by more`
  line `than one tenant holding severally it shall be lawful for the municipality, to recover from the owner of such`
  line `holding, any taxes payable under this Act by the occupier of the holding.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (40499)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 103
  title `Recovery by owner of occupier's tax paid by owner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40499&sectionno=103&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any tax shall be recovered`
  line `from any owner of any holding under the provisions of section 102, it shall be lawful for such owner, if`
  line `there shall be but one occupying tenant of such entire holding, to recover from such tenant of the entire`
  line `amount of the tax which shall have been so paid by such owner, and if there shall be one occupying tenant`
  line `of a part of such holding, or more than one occupying tenant of such holding then to recover from each tenant such sum as shall bear to the entire amount of tax which may have been so recovered from such`
  line `owner at the same proportion as the value of the proportion of such holding in the occupation of each`
  line `tenant bears to the entire value of such holding.`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (40500)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 104
  title `Method of recovery by owner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40500&sectionno=104&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `Every owner who under the provisions of section 102 may be`
  line `entitled to recover any sum from any occupying tenant of any holding or of any portion thereof, shall`
  line `have for the recovery of such sum all such and the same remedies, powers, rights and authorities as if`
  line `such sum were rent payable to such owner by such tenant in respect of so much of such holding as may be`
  line `in the occupation of such tenant.`
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (40501)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 105
  title Penalty.
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40501&sectionno=105&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `Whoever keeps or is in possession of any cart, carriage or animal without the licence`
  line `as required under this Act shall be liable to a fine not exceeding four times the fee payable by him in`
  line `respect of such licence, in addition to the licence fee due.`
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (40502)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 106
  title `Municipality may compound with livery stable keepers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40502&sectionno=106&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `The municipality, may compound`
  line `for any period not exceeding one year, with livery stablekeepers and other persons keeping carts,`
  line `carriages or animals for hire, for a certain sum to be paid for the carts, carriages or animal so kept by such`
  line `person in lieu of the licence fees specified in any order made by the municipality.`
obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (40503)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 107
  title `Rents, tolls and fees in respect of markets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40503&sectionno=107&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `(1) The municipality may use its own land or`
  line `building, or purchase, take on lease or otherwise acquire any land or building for the purpose of`
  line `establishing a municipal market or improving any existing municipal market.`
  line
  line `(2) The municipality may levy rents, tolls and fees at such rates as it may think proper for the right to`
  line `expose goods for sale in a municipal market and for the use of shops, stalls and standings therein and may`
  line `also regulate such rates in respect of private markets or places used or declared by the municipality as a`
  line `market place by a public notice in the locality.`
  line
  line `(3) The municipality may grant a lease for a period not exceeding three years for collection of rents,`
  line `tolls and fees in municipal markets at the rates fixed by the municipality under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) A lessee of a municipal market appointed under sub-section (3) may refuse to allow any person to`
  line `expose goods for sale in the market or to use shops, stalls and standings therein until the proper rents, tolls`
  line `and fees have been paid.`
  line
  line `(5) Whoever, having rendered himself liable to the payment of rents, tolls or fees refuses to pay the`
  line `same shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `(6) When resistance is offered to any person authorised to collect rents, tolls or fees, any police`
  line `officer whom he may call to his aid, shall be bound to assist him; and such police officer shall, for that`
  line `purpose have the same powers as he has in the exercise of his ordinary police duties.`
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  sectionId (40504)
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 108
  title `Recovery of taxes as arrears of land revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40504&sectionno=108&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any sum is due on account of a tax,`
  line `other than octroi or tolls or any similar tax payable upon immediate demand, from a person to a`
  line `municipality, the municipality may, without prejudice to any other mode of recovery provided in this Act`
  line `apply to the Deputy Commissioner to recover such sum together with costs of proceedings incurred in`
  line `that behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) The Deputy Commissioner, on being satisfied that the sum mentioned in the application under`
  line `sub-section (1) is due, shall proceed to recover it as soon as may be thereafter, as arrears of land revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (40505)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 109
  title `Power to sell unclaimed holdings for money due.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40505&sectionno=109&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line `(1) If money be due under this Act in`
  line `respect of any holding from the owner thereof, on account of any tax, expenses or charges recoverable`
  line `under this Act, if the owner of such holding or his whereabouts are unknown or the ownership thereof is`
  line `disputed or when the owner lives outside the municipality and has failed to pay it in spite of service of`
  line `demand notice twice, the municipality may publish twice, at an interval of three months, a notification of`
  line `sale of such holding and after the expiry of not less than three months from the date of the last`
  line `publication, unless the amount recoverable be paid, may sell such holding to the highest bidder, who`
  line `shall, at the time of sale, deposit forthwith twenty-five per cent, of the purchase money. The balance shall`
  line `be paid within fifteen days of the date of sale. In default of payment of the balance amount, the money if`
  line `any, so deposited shall be forfeited and the holding shall be re-sold. After deducting the amount due to the`
  line `municipality, the surplus sale-proceeds, if any, shall be credited to the municipal fund and may be paid on demand to any person who establishes his right of claim to the satisfaction of such municipality or in a`
  line `Court of competent jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person may pay the amount due at any time before the completion of the sale and may`
  line `recover such amount by a suit in a Court of competent jurisdiction from any person beneficially interested`
  line `in such property.`
obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (40506)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 110
  title `Writing off irrecoverable sums due to the Nagar Panchayat or to the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40506&sectionno=110&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line The
  line `irrecoverable sum due to a Nagar Panchayat, or as the case may be, to a Council may be written off in`
  line `such manner and by such authority as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (40507)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 111
  title `Power to make roads.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40507&sectionno=111&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Nagar Panchayat or as the case may be, a Council may--`
  line
  line `(a) layout or make new public road; or`
  line
  line `(b) widen, open, enlarge or otherwise improve any public road and construct tunnels and other`
  line `works subsidiary to such road; or`
  line
  line `(c) divert, discontinue or close permanently any public road; or`
  line
  line `(d) sell or lease the land forming such road or any part thereof, acquired for the purpose of such`
  line `road or for any other purpose of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such public road shall be discontinued, permanently closed or used for any other`
  line `purposes without the previous sanction of the Government.`
  line
  line `(2) In laying out, making, turning, diverting, widening, opening; enlarging or otherwise improving`
  line `any public road, the Nagar Panchayat or the Council may, in accordance with the provisions of this Act,`
  line `acquire land required for the carriage-way, footways and drains thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (40508)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 112
  title `Power to repair, etc., of private road, drains, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40508&sectionno=112&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a Nagar Panchayat or a Council`
  line `considers that in any road not being a public road, or in any part of such road within the municipality, it is`
  line `necessary for the public health, convenience or safety that any work should be done for the levelling,`
  line `paving, metalling, flagging, channelling, draining, lighting or cleaning thereof, the Nagar Panchayat or as`
  line `the case may be, the Council may, by written notice, require the owner or owners of the several lands or`
  line `buildings fronting or adjoining the said road or abutting thereon to carry out such work in such manner`
  line `and within such time as may be specified in such notice.`
  line
  line `(2) If the notice under sub-section (1) is not complied with, such work may be executed by the Nagar`
  line `Panchayat or the Council, the expenses thereby incurred, shall be apportioned by the Nagar Panchayat or`
  line `the Council, between such owners, and in such manner as it may think fit, regard being had, if it deems it`
  line `necessary, to the amount and value of any work already done by the owners or occupiers of such lands`
  line `and buildings.`
  line
  line `(3) After such work has been carried out by the owner or by the owners or on the failure of the`
  line `owners to do so, by the Nagar Panchayat or the Council at the expenses of such owners the road or part`
  line `thereof in which such work has been done, may, and on the joint requisition of a majority of the said`
  line `owners, shall be declared by public notice put up therein by the Nagar Panchayat or the Council to be a`
  line `public road.`
obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_113:
  sectionId (40509)
  sectionNo (113)
  orderNo 113
  title `Prohibition of use of public roads by a class of animals, carts or vehicles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_113_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40509&sectionno=113&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_113_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Nagar`
  line `Panchayat or as the case may be, the Council may, by public notice prohibit or regulate the driving, riding`
  line `or leading of animals or vehicles of any particular kind along any public road or part of any such road.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who disobeys an order passed by the Nagar Panchayat or as the case may be, the`
  line `Council under the provisions of sub-section (1) shall be punishable with fine not exceeding two hundred`
  line rupees.
obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_114:
  sectionId (40510)
  sectionNo (114)
  orderNo 114
  title `Penalty for encroachment on public roads, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40510&sectionno=114&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_114_content:
  string
  line `Any person, who without the permission of`
  line `the Nagar Panchayat or of the Council,--`
  line
  line `(a) encroaches upon any public road or house-gully or upon any public drain, sewer, aqueduct,`
  line `water-course or that by making any excavation or by erecting any wall, fence, rail, post, projection or`
  line `other obstruction, or by deposing any movable property thereon, or`
  line
  line `(b) takes up or alters the pavements or other materials, fences or posts on any public road,`
  line
  line `shall, for every such offence, be punishable with fine not exceeding two thousand and five hundred rupees`
  line `and with a further fine not exceeding two hundred rupees for every day during which the encroachment`
  line `continues after the first conviction.`
obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_115:
  sectionId (40511)
  sectionNo (115)
  orderNo 115
  title `Use of public road or place by vendors and other person and penalty thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_115_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40511&sectionno=115&orderno=115&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_115_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject`
  line `to the provisions of this Act and the rules and bye-laws made thereunder, no itinerant vendor or any other`
  line `person shall use or occupy any public road or place for the sale of articles or for the exercise of any`
  line `calling, or for setting up any booth or stall without the permission of the Nagar Panchayat or of the`
  line Council.
  line
  line `(2) Whoever violate the provision of sub-section (1) shall be punishable with fine which may extend`
  line `to two thousand five hundred rupees and with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees for every`
  line `subsequent offence after the first conviction.`
obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_116:
  sectionId (40512)
  sectionNo (116)
  orderNo 116
  title `Power to remove obstructions, encroachments and projections in or on public road, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40512&sectionno=116&orderno=116&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_116_content:
  string
  line `The Nagar Panchayat or as the case may be, the Council may, notwithstanding any proceedings which`
  line `may have been started against him under this Act, issue a notice requiring any person to remove any`
  line `building which he may have built or any fence, rail, post or other obstruction or encroachment which he`
  line `may have erected or stacked, on any part of a public road, house-gully, public drain, sewer, aqueduct,`
  line `watercourse, ghat or any land vested in the Nagar Panchayat or in the Council and, if such person fails to`
  line `comply with such requisition within forty-eight hours of the receipt of the same, the Sub-Divisional`
  line `Magistrate may, on the application of the Nagar Panchayat or of the Council, order that such obstruction`
  line `or encroachment be removed and thereupon the Nagar Panchayat or the Council may remove any such`
  line `obstruction of encroachment and the expenses thereby incurred shall be paid by the person who erected or`
  line `stacked the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_117:
  sectionId (40513)
  sectionNo (117)
  orderNo 117
  title `Procedure when person who erected obstruction cannot be found.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_117_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40513&sectionno=117&orderno=117&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_117_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the person who`
  line `built, erected or stacked the said building, fence, rail, post or other obstruction or encroachment referred`
  line `to in the preceding section is not known or cannot be found, the Nagar Panchayat or as the case may be,`
  line `the Council may cause a notice to be posted in the neighbourhood of the said building, fence, rail, post or`
  line `other obstruction or encroachment requiring any person interested in the same to remove it, and it shall`
  line `not be necessary to name any person in such requisition.`
  line
  line `(2) If the said building, fence, rail, post or other obstruction or encroachment be not removed in`
  line `compliance with the requisition contained in such notice within forty-eight hours of the posting of the`
  line `same, the Sub-Divisional Magistrate may, on the application of the Nagar Panchayat or as the case may`
  line `be, the Council, order that such obstruction or encroachment be removed, and thereupon the Nagar`
  line `Panchayat or as the case may be, the Council may remove any such obstruction or encroachment, and`
  line `may recover the cost of such removal, by sale of the materials so removed.`
  line
  line `(3) The surplus sale-proceeds, if any, shall be credited to the Municipal Fund, and may be paid on`
  line `demand to any person who established his right to the satisfaction of the Nagar Panchayat or as the case`
  line `may be, the Council or in any court of competent jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_118:
  sectionId (40514)
  sectionNo (118)
  orderNo 118
  title `Projections from buildings to be removed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_118_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40514&sectionno=118&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_118_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Nagar Panchayat or as the case may be,`
  line `the Council may issue a notice requiring the owner or occupier of any building to remove or alter any`
  line `projection, obstruction or encroachment erected or placed against or in front of such building, if the same`
  line `overhangs the public road or just into or any way projects or encroaches upon, or is an obstruction to the`
  line `safe and convenient passage along any public road or house-gully, or obstructs, or projects or encroaches`
  line `into or upon any drain, sewer or aqueduct in any public road or into or upon any public water-course or`
  line `ghat or any land in the Nagar Panchayat or the Council, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) If such owner or occupier fails to comply with such requisition within forty-eight hours of the`
  line `receipt of the notice, or within such further time as the Nagar Panchayat or the Council may allow the Sub-Divisional Magistrate may, on the application of Nagar Panchayat or of the Council, order that such`
  line `projection, obstruction or encroachment be removed or altered; and thereupon the Nagar Panchayat or the`
  line `Council may remove or alter such projection, obstruction or encroachment, and any reasonable expense`
  line `incurred for the purposes of such removal or alteration shall be recovered from the defaulting owner or`
  line occupier.
  line
  line `(3) If the expense of removing or altering any such structure or fixture is paid by the occupier of the`
  line `building, in any case in which the same was not erected by himself, he shall be entitled to deduct any`
  line `reasonable expense incurred for the purposes of such removal or alteration from the rent payable by him`
  line `to the owner of the building.`
obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_119:
  sectionId (40630)
  sectionNo (119)
  orderNo 119
  title `Power of the District Magistrate and Sub-Divisional Magistrate to remove encroachment summarily on requisition by the Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_119_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40630&sectionno=119&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_119_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in sections 116`
  line `and 118, a District Magistrate or a Sub-Divisional Magistrate shall, on being so required by the`
  line `Government, order any person responsible for any obstruction or encroachment or projection as specified`
  line `in sections 116 and 118 to remove or alter such obstruction or encroachment or projection within a period`
  line `of not less than forty-eight hours and on non-compliance the District Magistrate or the Sub-Divisional`
  line `Magistrate as the case may be, shall remove such obstruction or encroachment or projection and realise`
  line `the expenses, thereby incurred from the person concerned as fine in a Criminal Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case the person or persons responsible for such obstruction, encroachment or`
  line `projection is or are not known or cannot be found the procedure laid down in section 117 shall be`
  line followed.
obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_120:
  sectionId (40516)
  sectionNo (120)
  orderNo 120
  title `Effect of order made under section 116, 117, 118 or 119.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_120_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40516&sectionno=120&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_120_content:
  string
  line `Every order made by a SubDivisional Magistrate or a District Magistrate as the case may be, under section 116, 117, 118 or 119 shall`
  line `be deemed to be an order made by him in the discharge of his judicial duty and the Nagar Panchayat or as`
  line `the case may be, the Council shall be deemed to be person bound to execute such order within the`
  line `meaning of the Judicial Officers Protection Act, 1850 (Act XVII of 1850 ).`
obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_121:
  sectionId (40517)
  sectionNo (121)
  orderNo 121
  title `Nagar Panchayat or Council may require land holders to trim hedges, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_121_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40517&sectionno=121&orderno=121&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_121_content:
  string
  line `The Nagar`
  line `Panchayat or as the case may be, the Council may require the owner or occupier of any land within three`
  line `days to trim or prune the hedges thereon bordering on any public road or drains, and to cut and trim any`
  line `trees or bamboos thereon overhanging the public road, drain or tank, or any well used for drinking`
  line `purpose or obstructing any public road or drain or causing or likely to cause damage to any public road or`
  line `drain or any property of the Nagar Panchayat or of the Council or likely to cause damage to person using`
  line `any public road or likely to foul the water of any well or tank.`
obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_122:
  sectionId (40518)
  sectionNo (122)
  orderNo 122
  title `Penalty for disobeying requisition under section 116, 117, 118 or 119.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_122_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40518&sectionno=122&orderno=122&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_122_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being the`
  line `owner or occupier of any house on land within a municipality, fails to comply with a requisition issued by`
  line `the Nagar Panchayat or as the case may be, the Council under the provisions of section 116, 117, 118 or`
  line `119 shall be punishable with fine not exceeding two thousand rupees, and with a further fine not`
  line `exceeding one hundred rupees for every day during which the default is continued after the first`
  line conviction.
obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_123:
  sectionId (40519)
  sectionNo (123)
  orderNo 123
  title `Names of public roads and number of buildings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40519&sectionno=123&orderno=123&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_123_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Nagar Panchayat or as the case may`
  line `be, the Council may cause a name to be given to any public road and to be fixed in such place as it may`
  line `think fit, and may also cause a number to be affixed to every building, and in like manner may, from time`
  line `to time, cause such names and numbers to be altered.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who destroys, pulls down, defaces or alters any-name or number put up by the Nagar`
  line `Panchayat or as the case may be, the Council under sub-section (1) shall, for every such offence be`
  line `punishable with fine which may extend to two hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_124:
  sectionId (40520)
  sectionNo (124)
  orderNo 124
  title `Erection of building without sanction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_124_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40520&sectionno=124&orderno=124&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_124_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall erect, materially alter or re-erect`
  line `or commence to erect, materially alter or re-erect any building without the sanction of the Nagar`
  line `Panchayat or of the Council, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person who intends to erect, materially alter or re-erect any building shall give notice in`
  line `writing to the Nagar Panchayat or as the case may be, to the Council of such erection.`
  line
  line `(3) When bye-laws have been framed under this Act no notice under sub-section (2) shall be`
  line `considered to be valid until such notice has complied with the provision of the bye-laws.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--An alteration in a building for the purposes of this section and of bye-laws be deemed`
  line `to be material if it--`
  line
  line `(a) affects or is likely to affect prejudicially the stability or safety of the building, or the condition`
  line `of the building in respect of drainage, ventilation, sanitation or hygiene;`
  line
  line `(b) increase or diminishes the height or area covered by, or the cubical capacity of the building, or`
  line `of any room in the building.`
  line
  line `(4) In the municipalities where water works are maintained it shall be compulsory for persons`
  line `erecting or re-erecting buildings costing rupees two lakhs or more (excluding cost of land and of`
  line `improvement of land) to install sanitary latrines. The municipality shall withhold sanction if the plan and`
  line `specification of the building submitted with the notice do not contain provision for installation of sanitary`
  line latrines.
obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_125:
  sectionId (40521)
  sectionNo (125)
  orderNo 125
  title `Special provision for cases where bye-laws have not been made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_125_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40521&sectionno=125&orderno=125&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_125_content:
  string
  line `In any case in which no`
  line `bye-laws have been made under this Act the Nagar Panchayat or as the case may be, the Council may,`
  line `within fourteen days of the receipt of the notice required by sub-section (2) of section 124, require a`
  line `person who has given such notice to furnish, within one week of the receipt by him of the requisition,`
  line `information on all or any of the matters as to which bye-laws might have been made and in such case the`
  line `notice shall not be valid until such information has been furnished.`
obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_126:
  sectionId (40522)
  sectionNo (126)
  orderNo 126
  title `Powers of Nagar Panchayat or the Council to sanction or refuse.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_126_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40522&sectionno=126&orderno=126&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_126_content:
  string
  line `(1) Within sixty days`
  line `after the receipt of the notice, required by sub-section (2) of section 124, the Nagar Panchayat or as the`
  line `case may be, the Council may refuse to sanction the building or may sanction it either absolutely or`
  line `subject to such modification as it may deem fit in respect of all or any of the matters specified in`
  line `bye-laws and the person erecting, materially altering or re-erecting any such building as aforesaid shall`
  line `comply with the sanction of the Nagar Panchayat or as the case may be, the Council as granted in every`
  line particular.
  line
  line `(2) When within a period of sixty days, the Nagar Panchayat or the Council fails, after the receipt of a`
  line `valid notice, to make and deliver to the person who has given such notice, an order of sanction or refusal`
  line `in respect thereof, it shall be deemed to have sanctioned the proposal of building absolutely:`
  line
  line `Provided that the time taken by the applicant in furnishing any information requisitioned by the Nagar`
  line `Panchayat or by the Council, if any, after the receipt of the valid notice shall not be counted in the period`
  line `of sixty days referred to in this sub-section.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--The Nagar Panchayat or the Council may refuse to sanction the erection, material`
  line `alteration or re-erection of any building either on the grounds affecting the particular building or in`
  line `pursuance of general scheme adopted by the Nagar Panchayat or by the Council at a meeting restricting`
  line `the erection or re-erection of building or any class of building within specified limits for the prevention of`
  line `overcrowding or in the interest of the residents within such limits or for any other public purpose.`
  line `Permission may also be refused in any case in which there is any dispute between the Nagar Panchayat or`
  line `as the case may be, the Council and the applicant as to the title of the land on which it is proposed to erect`
  line `the building until such dispute is decided.`
obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_127:
  sectionId (40523)
  sectionNo (127)
  orderNo 127
  title `Lapse of sanction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40523&sectionno=127&orderno=127&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_127_content:
  string
  line `A permission to erect, materially alter or re-erect building granted under`
  line `this Chapter or deemed to have been given by the Nagar Panchayat or as the case may be, the Council,`
  line `shall unless it is renewed on an application made to the Nagar Panchayat or the Council for this purpose`
  line `continue only for one year after the date on which it is granted.`
obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_128:
  sectionId (40524)
  sectionNo (128)
  orderNo 128
  title `Penalty for building without or in contravention of sanction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_128_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40524&sectionno=128&orderno=128&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_128_content:
  string
  line `Whoever erects, materially`
  line `alters or re-erects or commences to erect, materially alter or re-erect any building without the previous`
  line `sanction of the Nagar Panchayat or as the case may be, the Council or in contravention of any directions`
  line `given by the Nagar Panchayat or as the case may be, the Council granting sanction under section 123`
  line `shall be liable to a fine not exceeding one thousand rupees for every such offence, and to a further fine not`
  line `exceeding two hundred rupees for each day during which the offence is continued after his first`
  line conviction.
obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_129:
  sectionId (40525)
  sectionNo (129)
  orderNo 129
  title `Power of a Nagar Panchayat or a Council in case of disobedience.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40525&sectionno=129&orderno=129&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_129_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the construction of`
  line `a building is started, or if a building is materially altered or erected--`
  line
  line `(a) without sanction as required by section 126 (1); or`
  line
  line `(b) without notice as required by section 124 (2); or`
  line
  line `(c) when sanction has been refused; or`
  line
  line `(d) in contravention of the terms of any sanction granted; or`
  line
  line `(e) when the sanction has lapsed; or`
  line
  line `(f) in contravention of any bye-laws made under clause (vi) of sub-section (1) of section 209,`
  line
  line `the Nagar Panchayat or as the case may be, or the Council may, by notice to be delivered within a`
  line `reasonable time, require the building to be altered or demolished as it may deem necessary, within the`
  line `period of thirty days from the date of the service of such notice:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Nagar Panchayat or as the case may be, or the Council may instead of requiring the`
  line `alteration or demolition of any such building accept by way of composition such sum as it may deem`
  line reasonable.
  line
  line `(2) Any person who fails to comply with a requisition issued by the Nagar Panchayat or as the case`
  line `may be, or the Council under the provisions of sub-section (1) shall be liable to a fine not exceeding five`
  line `hundred rupees and to a further fine not exceeding one hundred rupees for every day during which the`
  line `person continues to make such default after service on him of such requisition.`
obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_130:
  sectionId (40526)
  sectionNo (130)
  orderNo 130
  title `Roofs and external walls not to be made of inflammable materials.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40526&sectionno=130&orderno=130&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_130_content:
  string
  line `The Nagar Panchayat`
  line `or as the case may be, the Council by written notice, may require any person who has made any external`
  line `roof or wall with thatch mats, leaves or other inflammable materials and in contravention of bye-laws`
  line `made under section 209 to remove or alter such roof or wall within a period to be specified in the notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_131:
  sectionId (40527)
  sectionNo (131)
  orderNo 131
  title `Power to attach brackets for lamps.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40527&sectionno=131&orderno=131&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_131_content:
  string
  line `The Nagar Panchayat or as the case may be, the Council`
  line `may, attach or cause to be attached to the outside of any building brackets for lamps in such manner as`
  line `not to occasion any injury thereto or inconvenience.`
obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_132:
  sectionId (40528)
  sectionNo (132)
  orderNo 132
  title `Building unfit for human habitation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_132_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40528&sectionno=132&orderno=132&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_132_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a building, or a room in a building is in the`
  line `opinion of the Nagar Panchayat or as the case may be, the Council unfit for human habitation in`
  line `consequence of the want of proper means of drains or ventilation or otherwise, the Nagar Panchayat or as`
  line `the case may be, the Council may, by notice, prohibit the owner or occupier thereof from using the`
  line `building or room for human habitation or suffering it to be so used whether absolutely or not unless,`
  line `within a time to be specified in the notice he effects such alteration therein as is specified in the notice.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon failure of a person to whom notice is issued under sub-section (1) to comply therewith, the`
  line `Nagar Panchayat or as the case may be, the Council may require by further notice the demolition of the`
  line `building or room.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person who uses a building or room or suffers to be used contrary to the provision of`
  line `sub-section (1) shall be punishable with fine not exceeding five hundred rupees, and with a further fine`
  line `not exceeding one hundred rupees for every day during which the offence is continued after the first`
  line conviction.
obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_133:
  sectionId (40529)
  sectionNo (133)
  orderNo 133
  title `Pending of building in dangerous state.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_133_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40529&sectionno=133&orderno=133&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_133_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Nagar Panchayat or as the case may be, a`
  line `Council may require by notice the owner or occupier of any land or building--`
  line
  line `(a) to demolish, secure or repair within eight days from the date of service of the notice in such`
  line `manner as it deems necessary any building, portion of a building, wall or other structure or anything`
  line `affixed thereto which appears to it to be in ruinous condition or dangerous to inmates if any,`
  line `passers-by or other property, or`
  line
  line `(b) to repair, secure or enclose, within eight days from the date of service of the notice, in such`
  line `manner as it deems necessary any tank, well or excavation belonging to such owner or in the`
  line `possession of such occupier which appear to the Nagar Panchayat or the Council to be dangerous to`
  line `persons by reason of its situation, want of repairs or other such circumstances.`
  line
  line `(2) Where it appears to the Nagar Panchayat or the Council that immediate action is necessary for the`
  line `purpose of preventing imminent danger to any person or property, it shall be the duty of the Nagar`
  line `Panchayat or as the case may be, of the Council to take immediate action and recover the expense so`
  line `incurred from the owner or occupier of the building or the owner or occupier of the land to which such`
  line `building or other structure or anything is affixed.`
obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_134:
  sectionId (40530)
  sectionNo (134)
  orderNo 134
  title `Nagar Panchayat or Council may require owners to pull down ruins.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_134_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40530&sectionno=134&orderno=134&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_134_content:
  string
  line `Whenever it appears`
  line `to the Nagar Panchayat or Council that any building by reason of abandonment or disputed ownership or`
  line `other cause is undaunted or by reason of having fallen into ruins, affords facilities for the commission of a`
  line `nuisance by disorderly persons or for the harbouring of snakes or other noxious animals, the Nagar`
  line `Panchayat or the Council may require the owner of such building or the land to which such building is`
  line `attached, to properly secure the same, or to remove or level such ruins, as the case may require.`
obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_135:
  sectionId (40531)
  sectionNo (135)
  orderNo 135
  title `Penalty for disobeying requisition under sections 133 and 134.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40531&sectionno=135&orderno=135&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_135_content:
  string
  line `Any owner or occupier of a`
  line `house or land who fails to comply with requisition issued by the Nagar Panchayat or the Council under`
  line `the provisions of sections 133 and 134, shall be liable, for every such default, to a penalty not exceeding`
  line `one thousand rupees, and to a further penalty not exceeding two hundred rupees, for every day during`
  line `which the default is continued after the expiry of eight days from the date of service on him of such`
  line requisition.
obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_136:
  sectionId (40532)
  sectionNo (136)
  orderNo 136
  title `Compensation for prohibition of erection or re-erection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_136_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40532&sectionno=136&orderno=136&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_136_content:
  string
  line `Subject to any other provision in`
  line `this Act as regard compensation, no compensations shall be claimable by an owner for any damage which`
  line `he may sustain in consequence of the prohibition of the erection of any building.`
obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_137:
  sectionId (40533)
  sectionNo (137)
  orderNo 137
  title `Power to require owners to clear noxious vegetation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_137_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40533&sectionno=137&orderno=137&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_137_content:
  string
  line `The Nagar Panchayat or the Council`
  line `may, by notice, require the owner or occupier of any land within such time as the Nagar Panchayat or the`
  line `Council may fix to cut and remove any tree or bamboos or branches thereof, or eradicate and destroy`
  line `vegetation and undergrowth which may appear to the Nagar Panchayat or the Council to be insanitary,`
  line `injurious to health or offensive to the neighbourhood or to be causing or likely to cause damage or`
  line `destruction to any crop growing or to be grown, or to be obstruction or likely to obstruct the free passage`
  line `for men or animals along a public road, or of any boat of stream vessel along a public water way.`
obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_138:
  sectionId (40534)
  sectionNo (138)
  orderNo 138
  title `Power to require owners to improve bad drainage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_138_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40534&sectionno=138&orderno=138&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_138_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any land, being private`
  line `property or within any private enclosure, appears to the Nagar Panchayat or the Council by want of`
  line `drainage to be in a state injurious to health or offensive to the neighbourhood, or by reason of inequalities`
  line `of a surface to afford facilities for the commission of a nuisance, the Nagar Panchayat or the Council may`
  line `require the owner or the occupier of such land or both within fifteen days, to drain such land or level`
  line `surface:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if for the purpose of effecting any drainage under this section it shall be necessary to`
  line `acquire any land not being the property of the person who is required to drain his land, or to pay`
  line `compensation to any other person, the Nagar Panchayat or as the case may be, the Council shall provide`
  line `such land and pay such compensation.`
obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_139:
  sectionId (40535)
  sectionNo (139)
  orderNo 139
  title `Power to require unwholesome tanks or private premises to be cleansed or drained.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_139_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40535&sectionno=139&orderno=139&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_139_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `The Nagar Panchayat or the Council may require the owner or occupier of any land within eight days or`
  line `such longer period as the Nagar Panchayat or the Council may fix, either to re-excavate or at his option`
  line `fill up with suitable material or to cleanse any well, water-course, private tank or pool therein, and to`
  line `drain off and remove any waste or stagnant water which may appear to be injurious to health or offensive`
  line `to the neighbourhood:`
  line
  line `Provided that if, for the purpose of effecting any drainage under this section, it shall be necessary to`
  line `acquire any land not being the property of the person who is required to drain his land or to pay`
  line `compensation to any other person, Nagar Panchayat or as the case may be, the Council shall provide such`
  line `land and pay such compensation.`
  line
  line `(2) If under the provisions of this Act the Nagar Panchayat or the Council execute the work of such`
  line `re-excavation or filling up with suitable material, it may take possession of the tank or pool or the sites of`
  line `such tank or pool and retain such possession and turn the same to profitable account until the expenses`
  line `thereby incurred shall have been realised.`
obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_140:
  sectionId (40536)
  sectionNo (140)
  orderNo 140
  title `Wells, tanks, etc., to be secured.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_140_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40536&sectionno=140&orderno=140&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_140_content:
  string
  line `If any well, tank or other excavation, whether on public or`
  line `private ground, be, for want of sufficient repair or protection, dangerous to passers by the Nagar`
  line `Panchayat or as the case may be, the Council shall forthwith require by notice such owner or occupier, or`
  line `both within eight days, properly to secure or protect such well, tank or other excavation; and if after the`
  line `said period the work is not executed, the Nagar Panchayat or as the case may be, the Council shall cause a`
  line `temporary hoard or fence to be put for the protection of passers-by and recover the expenses so incurred`
  line `from the owner or occupier or the owners and occupiers of the land on which such tank, well or other`
  line `excavation is situated.`
obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_141:
  sectionId (40537)
  sectionNo (141)
  orderNo 141
  title `Penalty for disobeying requisition under sections 137, 138, 139 and 140.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_141_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40537&sectionno=141&orderno=141&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_141_content:
  string
  line `Any owner or`
  line `occupier of a house or land who fails to comply with a requisition issued by the Nagar Panchayat or the`
  line `Council under the provisions of section 137, 138, 139 or 140 shall be punishable with fine not exceeding`
  line `one thousand rupees, and with a further fine not exceeding two hundred rupees for every day during`
  line `which the default is continued after the expiry of eight days from the date of service on him of such`
  line requisition.
obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_142:
  sectionId (40538)
  sectionNo (142)
  orderNo 142
  title `Power of Government to prohibit cultivation, use of manure, or irrigation injurious to health.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_142_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40538&sectionno=142&orderno=142&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_142_content:
  string
  line `If the Director of Medical Health and Family Planning Services, Public Health Officer of the`
  line `Government or Health Officer of the municipality or such other Medical Officer of the Medical`
  line `Department of Manipur as may be prescribed, certifies that the cultivation of any description of crops, or`
  line `the use of any kind of manure, or the irrigation of land in any specified manner--`
  line
  line `(a) in any place within the limit of the municipality, is injurious to the health of person dwelling`
  line `in the neighbourhood; or`
  line
  line `(b) in any place within or without the limits of the municipality is likely to contaminate the water`
  line `supply of the municipality or otherwise renders it unfit for drinking purposes the Government, on`
  line `receipt of an application from the municipality by public notice, prohibit the cultivation of such crop,`
  line `the use of manure or the use of the method of irrigation so certified to be injurious, or impose such`
  line `conditions with respect thereto as may prevent the injury`
obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_143:
  sectionId (40539)
  sectionNo (143)
  orderNo 143
  title `Public latrines and urinals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_143_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40539&sectionno=143&orderno=143&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_143_content:
  string
  line `The municipality may provide and maintain in sufficient number`
  line `and in proper situation, public latrines and urinals for the separate use of each sex, and shall cause the`
  line `same to be kept in proper order and to be properly cleansed.`
obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_144:
  sectionId (40540)
  sectionNo (144)
  orderNo 144
  title `Power to demolish unauthorised drains leading into public.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_144_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40540&sectionno=144&orderno=144&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_144_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person, without the`
  line `written permission of the municipality first obtained, marks or causes to be made, or alters or causes to be`
  line `altered, any drain leading into any sewer, drain, water-course, road or land vested in the municipality, the`
  line `municipality may cause such branch drain to be demolished, altered, made or otherwise dealt with as it`
  line `may deem fit, and the expenses thereby incurred shall be paid by such person, making or altering such`
  line `branch drain.`
  line
  line `(2) The person so making or altering such branch drain shall also be liable for every such offence to a`
  line `fine not exceeding five hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_145:
  sectionId (40541)
  sectionNo (145)
  orderNo 145
  title `Penalty for allowing water of any sewer, etc., to run on any public road.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_145_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40541&sectionno=145&orderno=145&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_145_content:
  string
  line `Whoever causes`
  line `or allows the water of any sink, sewer, latrine, urinal, cesspool or any other offensive matter belonging to`
  line `him or being on his land to run, drain or be thrown or put upon any public road, or causes or allows any`
  line `offensive matter to run, drain or be thrown into a surface drain near any public road shall be liable to a`
  line `fine not exceeding two hundred rupees and a daily fine not exceeding fifty rupees during which the`
  line `offence is continued.`
obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_146:
  sectionId (40542)
  sectionNo (146)
  orderNo 146
  title `Power to require owner to drain land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_146_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40542&sectionno=146&orderno=146&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_146_content:
  string
  line `If any land, near a sewer, drain or other outlet into`
  line `which such land may, in the opinion of the Nagar Panchayat or as the case may be, the Council, be`
  line `drained, is not drained to the satisfaction of the Nagar Panchayat or as the case may be, of the Council, it`
  line `may require the owner within one month to drain the said land into such sewer, drain or outlet.`
obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_147:
  sectionId (40543)
  sectionNo (147)
  orderNo 147
  title `Penalty for disobeying requisition under section 146.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_147_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40543&sectionno=147&orderno=147&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_147_content:
  string
  line `Any person who fails to comply with`
  line `a requisition issued by the Nagar Panchayat or, as the case may be, by the Council under the provision of`
  line `section 146 shall be liable for every such offence, to a fine not exceeding two hundred rupees and a`
  line `further fine not exceeding fifty rupees for every day during which he shall continue to make such default`
  line `after service on him of such requisition.`
obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_148:
  sectionId (40544)
  sectionNo (148)
  orderNo 148
  title `Establishment for removal of sewage, offensive matter and rubbish.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_148_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40544&sectionno=148&orderno=148&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_148_content:
  string
  line `The Nagar Panchayat`
  line `or, as the case may be, the Council shall provide for the removal--`
  line
  line `(a) of sewage, rubbish and offensive matter from all public latrines, urinals and drains and from`
  line `all public roads and all other property vested in the municipality, and`
  line
  line `(b) in any municipality wherein a latrine tax has been imposed under sub-section (1) of section 75`
  line `of sewage and offensive matter from all private latrines, privies, urinals, cesspools and compounds.`
obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_149:
  sectionId (40545)
  sectionNo (149)
  orderNo 149
  title `Sewerage scheme.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_149_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40545&sectionno=149&orderno=149&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_149_content:
  string
  line `A municipality may also introduce a sewerage scheme for removal of`
  line `sewage by flushing with water through underground closed sewers. When a municipality introduces such`
  line `a scheme in its area the municipality may, where it is felt necessary, with the approval of the State`
  line `Government, levy additional latrine and water taxes to meet the cost and maintenance of such scheme.`
obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_150:
  sectionId (40546)
  sectionNo (150)
  orderNo 150
  title `Removal of sewage, offensive material, rubbish.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_150_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40546&sectionno=150&orderno=150&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_150_content:
  string
  line `(1) The municipality may, from time to`
  line `time, by an order published in the prescribed manner, appoint the hour within which sewage and offensive`
  line `matter may be moved, the manner in which the same shall be moved, as also the hours within which only`
  line `every occupier of any house or land may place rubbish in a receptacle provided by the municipality on or`
  line `by the side of the public road.`
  line
  line `(2) The municipality may provide places convenient for the deposit of sewage and offensive matter`
  line `and require the occupiers of houses to cause the same to be deposited daily or at other stated intervals in`
  line `such places, and may remove the same at the expense of the occupiers from any house if the occupier`
  line `thereof fails to do so.`
obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_151:
  sectionId (40547)
  sectionNo (151)
  orderNo 151
  title `Penalty for placing rubbish on public road.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_151_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40547&sectionno=151&orderno=151&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_151_content:
  string
  line `Any person who places or allows to place`
  line `rubbish on a public road or in a receptacle provided by the municipality at a time other than the time`
  line `appointed by the municipality under sub-section (1) of section 150 shall, for every such offence, be`
  line `punishable with fine not exceeding five hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_152:
  sectionId (40548)
  sectionNo (152)
  orderNo 152
  title `Penalty on occupier for not removing filth, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_152_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40548&sectionno=152&orderno=152&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_152_content:
  string
  line `Any occupier of a house on or near a public`
  line `road who keeps or allows to be kept, for more than twenty-four hours, or for more than such shorter time`
  line `as may be appointed by the municipality, otherwise than in some proper receptable, any house, ashes,`
  line `sewage or any noxious or offensive matter in or upon such house, or in any out-house, yard or ground`
  line `attached to and occupied with the house or suffers such receptacle to be in a filthy or noxious state, or`
  line `neglects to employ means to cleanse the same shall, be punishable with fine not exceeding five hundred`
  line rupees.
obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_153:
  sectionId (40549)
  sectionNo (153)
  orderNo 153
  title `Penalty for throwing offensive matter on public roads, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_153_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40549&sectionno=153&orderno=153&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_153_content:
  string
  line `Any person who, without the`
  line `permission of the municipality throws or puts, or permits his servants to throw or put any sewage or`
  line `offensive matter on any public road, or who throws or puts or permits his servants to throw or put, any`
  line `earth, rubbish, sewage or offensive matter into any drain communicating therewith shall be punishable`
  line `with fine not exceeding five hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_154:
  sectionId (40550)
  sectionNo (154)
  orderNo 154
  title `Power of servants of the Nagar Panchayat or of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_154_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40550&sectionno=154&orderno=154&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_154_content:
  string
  line `All servants of the Nagar`
  line `Panchayat, or as the case may be, of the Council employed for the purposes mentioned in section 163`
  line `may, within such hours as may be fixed by the Nagar Panchayat or the Council, enter any premises, of`
  line `which the occupier or owner is liable to pay latrine tax and do all things necessary for the performance of`
  line `their duties.`
obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_155:
  sectionId (40551)
  sectionNo (155)
  orderNo 155
  title `Supply of drinking water.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_155_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40551&sectionno=155&orderno=155&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_155_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Nagar Panchayat or as the case may be, the Council`
  line `shall provide or arrange for the provision of a sufficient supply of drinking water for the inhabitants of the`
  line `areas within its jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Nagar Panchayat or as the case may be, the Council shall provide sufficient and regular`
  line `supply of drinking water fit for human consumption or for domestic purposes within the jurisdiction of`
  line `the Nagar Panchayat or of the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_156:
  sectionId (40552)
  sectionNo (156)
  orderNo 156
  title `Removal of latrines, etc., near any source of water supply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_156_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40552&sectionno=156&orderno=156&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_156_content:
  string
  line `The municipality may, by`
  line `notice, require an owner or occupier on whose land a drain, privy, latrine, urinal, cesspool or other receptacle for filth or refuse exists as is likely to endanger the purity of water, a spring, well, tank,`
  line `reservoir or other source from which water is, or may be, derived for public use, to remove or close the`
  line `same within one week from the service of such notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_157:
  sectionId (40553)
  sectionNo (157)
  orderNo 157
  title `Owner or occupier to take steps to prevent spread of infectious disease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_157_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40553&sectionno=157&orderno=157&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_157_content:
  string
  line `In the event of a`
  line `municipality, or any part thereof, being visited with an outbreak of cholera or other infectious disease`
  line `notified in this behalf, the owner or occupier may during the continuance of the epidemic, without notice`
  line `and at any time, inspect and disinfect any well, tank or other place from which water, is or is likely to be`
  line `taken for the purpose of drinking and may further take such step as he deems fit to prevent the removal of`
  line `water therefrom.`
obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_158:
  sectionId (40554)
  sectionNo (158)
  orderNo 158
  title `Unauthorised construction or tree over drain or water-works.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_158_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40554&sectionno=158&orderno=158&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_158_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any road or way`
  line `has been made or any building, wall or other structure has been erected or any tree has been planted over`
  line `a public drain culvert or a water-work vested in the municipality, without the permission in writing of the`
  line `municipality, the municipality may without prejudice to the generality of the other provision of this Act--`
  line
  line `(a) by notice require the person who has made the road, erected the structure or planted the tree,`
  line `or the owner or occupier of the land on which, the road has been made, structure erected or tree`
  line `planted, to remove or deal in any other way as the municipality thinks fit with the road, structure or`
  line `tree; or`
  line
  line `(b) itself remove or deal in any other way as it thinks fit with the road, structure or tree.`
  line
  line `(2) Any expense incurred by a municipality for action taken under clause (b) of sub-section (1) shall`
  line `be recoverable from the person by whom the road or way made, structure erected or tree planted.`
obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_159:
  sectionId (40555)
  sectionNo (159)
  orderNo 159
  title `Powers in respect of burial and burning places.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_159_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40555&sectionno=159&orderno=159&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_159_content:
  string
  line `(1) The municipality may, from time to`
  line `time, out of the Municipal fund, provide suitable places to be used as burial or burning grounds either`
  line `within or without the limits of the municipality and may charge such fees on the persons using the places`
  line `as may be fixed by bye-laws which may be framed in that behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) The municipality may, by public notice, order any burial or burning ground situated within`
  line `municipal limits or any municipal burial or burning ground outside such limits which is certified by the`
  line `Director of Medical, Health and Family Planning Service or a Public Health Officer of the State`
  line `Government or a Health Officer of the municipality to be dangerous to the health of persons living in the`
  line `neighbourhood, to be closed, from a date to be specified in the notice, and shall, in such case, if no`
  line `suitable place for burial or burning exists within a reasonable distance, provide a fitting place for the`
  line purpose.
  line
  line `(3) If any person, without the permission of the municipality bury or burn any corpse, or permit, to be`
  line `buried or burnt, any corpse at any place which is not any burial or burning ground made or formed`
  line `according to the provisions of this section, or after the date fixed thereunder for closing the same, he shall`
  line `be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `(4) Private burial places may be exempted from the order subject to such conditions as the`
  line `municipality may impose in this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that the limits of such burial places are sufficiently defined and that they shall only be used`
  line `for the burial of members of the family of the owners thereof.`
  line
  line `(5) No private burial or burning ground shall be made or formed within the municipality after the`
  line `commencement of this Act, without the permission in writing of the municipality.`
obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_160:
  sectionId (40556)
  sectionNo (160)
  orderNo 160
  title `Burial of paupers and unclaimed dead bodies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_160_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40556&sectionno=160&orderno=160&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_160_content:
  string
  line `The municipality may from time to time, out`
  line `of the Municipal fund, provide for the burial or burning of paupers and unclaimed dead bodies, free of`
  line `charge, within the limits of the municipality or otherwise arrange to dispose of as it thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_161:
  sectionId (40557)
  sectionNo (161)
  orderNo 161
  title `Powers to cause corpses to be burnt or buried according to the religious tenets of the deceased.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_161_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40557&sectionno=161&orderno=161&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_161_content:
  string
  line `After the expiration of not less than twenty-four hours from the death of any person, the`
  line `Nagar Panchayat or as the case may be, Council may cause the corpse of such person to be burnt or`
  line `buried, and the expenses thereby incurred shall be recoverable as a debt due from the estate of such person. In every such case, the corpse shall be disposed of, so far as may be possible in manner consistent`
  line `with the religious tenets of the deceased.`
obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_162:
  sectionId (40558)
  sectionNo (162)
  orderNo 162
  title `Establishment of markets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_162_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40558&sectionno=162&orderno=162&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_162_content:
  string
  line `A municipality may establish and maintain markets at suitable`
  line `places of the Municipality for the convenience of the people.`
obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_163:
  sectionId (40559)
  sectionNo (163)
  orderNo 163
  title `Power to remove persons from municipal market.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_163_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40559&sectionno=163&orderno=163&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_163_content:
  string
  line `If any officer specially empowered in`
  line `this behalf by the Nagar Panchayat or by the Council is satisfied that any person occupying any stall or`
  line `space in any municipal market is in unauthorised occupation of the stall or space or continues to occupy`
  line `the stall or space after authority to occupy has ceased, he may, with the previous sanction of the Nagar`
  line `Panchayat or of the Council, require such person to vacate the stall or space within such time as may be`
  line `mentioned in the requisition and such person may, in addition to any penalty to which he may be liable`
  line `under this Act, be summarily removed from the stall or space.`
obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_164:
  sectionId (40560)
  sectionNo (164)
  orderNo 164
  title `Places for slaughter of animals for sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_164_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40560&sectionno=164&orderno=164&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_164_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Nagar Panchayat or, as the case may be, the`
  line `Council may, and when required by the Government shall fix places with the approval of the State`
  line `Government for slaughter of animals for sale, and the Nagar Panchayat or Council may grant and`
  line `withdraw licence for the use of such premises, or, if they vest in the Nagar Panchayat or Council, may`
  line `charge rent for fees of the use of the places.`
  line
  line `(2) When any such premises have been fixed, no person shall slaughter any such animal for sale`
  line `within the Municipal area at any other place.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person who slaughters for sale any animals at any place within the Municipal area other than`
  line `the one fixed by the Nagar Panchayat or as the case may be, the Council under this section shall be`
  line `punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_165:
  sectionId (40561)
  sectionNo (165)
  orderNo 165
  title `Inspection before and after slaughter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_165_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40561&sectionno=165&orderno=165&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_165_content:
  string
  line `A Nagar Panchayat or, as the case may be, the`
  line `Council shall arrange for inspection of the animal by a Veterinary Surgeon or a competent person before`
  line `the animal is killed and may also arrange for inspection of the meat and organs for the purpose of`
  line `certification, as may be laid down by bye-laws of the meat for use as food.`
obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_166:
  sectionId (40562)
  sectionNo (166)
  orderNo 166
  title `Licencing of butcher.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_166_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40562&sectionno=166&orderno=166&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_166_content:
  string
  line `No person shall carry on the profession of a butcher except under a`
  line `licence from the municipality.`
obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_167:
  sectionId (40563)
  sectionNo (167)
  orderNo 167
  title `Regulation of offensive trades.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_167_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40563&sectionno=167&orderno=167&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_167_content:
  string
  line `(1) If it is shown to the satisfaction of a Nagar Panchayat or of`
  line `a Council that any building or place within the limits of the Municipality which any person uses or`
  line `intends to use as a factory or other place of business for the manufacture, storage, treatment or disposal of`
  line `any article, by reason of such use, or by reason of such intended use, occasions or is likely to cause a`
  line `public nuisance, the Nagar Panchayat or the Council may at its option require by notice the owner or`
  line `occupier of the building or place--`
  line
  line `(a) to desist or refrain, as the case may be, from using, or allowing to be used, the building or`
  line `place for such purpose, or`
  line
  line `(b) only to use, or allow to be used, the building or place for such purpose under such conditions`
  line `or after such structural alterations as the Nagar Panchayat or the Council imposes or prescribes in the`
  line `notice with the object of rendering the use of the building or place for such purpose free from`
  line objection.
  line
  line `(2) Whoever, after receiving a notice given under sub-section (1), uses or allows to be used any`
  line `building or place in contravention of the notice shall be punishable with fine which may extend to four`
  line `hundred rupees for every day on which he so uses or allows to be used the place or building after the date`
  line `of the first conviction.`
obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_168:
  sectionId (40631)
  sectionNo (168)
  orderNo 168
  title `Certain offensive and dangerous trades not to be established within the limits to be fixed by the municipality without licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_168_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40631&sectionno=168&orderno=168&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_168_content:
  string
  line `(1)Within such local limits as may be fixed by the municipality no place shall be used without a licence from the municipality which shall be renewable annually, for any`
  line `of the following purposes, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) melting tallow;`
  line
  line `(b) boiling offal or blood;`
  line
  line `(c) skinning or disembowelling animal;`
  line
  line `(d) the manufacture of bricks, pottery, tiles or lime in a klin, panja or lamp or by any other`
  line `similiar method;`
  line
  line `(e) as a soap-house, oil-boiling house, dyeing house;`
  line
  line `(f) as tannery, slaughter-house;`
  line
  line `(g) as a manufactory or place of business from which offensive or unwholesome odour may arise;`
  line
  line `(h) as a yard or depot for hay, straw, bamboo, thatching grass, jute or other dangerously`
  line `inflammable material for the purpose of any trade;`
  line
  line `(i) any store-house for kerosene, petroleum napthamcoal-tar or any inflammable oil or wholesale`
  line `stock of matches exceeding one hundred gross;`
  line
  line `(j) as a shop for the sale of meat;`
  line
  line `(k) as a place for the storage of rags or bones, or both;`
  line
  line `(l) tea stall;`
  line
  line `(m) sweetmeat stall;`
  line
  line `(n) hotel or eating house;`
  line
  line `(o) aerated water;`
  line
  line `(p) bakery, including biscuit factory.`
  line
  line `(2) Such licence shall not be withheld unless the municipality has reason to believe that the business`
  line `which it is intended to establish or maintain would be offensive or dangerous to persons residing in or`
  line `frequenting the neighbourhood.`
  line
  line `(3) The municipality may, subject, to such restrictions, if any, as it may impose, extend the provisions`
  line `of this section to yards or depots for trade in coal, coke, timber or wood.`
  line
  line `(4) The grant of a licence for the purposes mentioned in clause (i) of sub-section (1) shall be`
  line `consistent with the provision of the Petroleum Act, 1934 (30 of 1934) and no such licences shall be`
  line `granted unless the said provisions have been complied with by the applicant for the licence.`
obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_169:
  sectionId (40565)
  sectionNo (169)
  orderNo 169
  title `Cinemas, dramatic performances, circuses, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_169_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40565&sectionno=169&orderno=169&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_169_content:
  string
  line `(1) No place within a municipality shall be`
  line `kept open for the purposes of regular gain or otherwise by means of public cinematographic exhibitions,`
  line `dramatic performances, circuses, variety shows, or for purposes of public resort for similar recreations or`
  line `amusements unless a licence has been granted therefor by the municipality, which licence shall be`
  line `annually renewable and in accordance with such conditions as the municipality, subject to rules, may`
  line `deem fit to impose:`
  line
  line `Provided that such conditions shall not be inconsistent with the terms of any licence which may be`
  line `required for such place under any other Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No place within the municipality shall be used for the purposes of public cinematographic,`
  line `performance, circus, variety shows, or as a place of public resort for similar recreations or amusements,`
  line `otherwise than for the purpose of regular gain, unless a licence has been granted for such purpose by the`
  line `municipality and in accordance with such conditions as the municipality, subject to rules, may think fit to`
  line `impose:`
  line
  line `Provided that such conditions shall not be inconsistent with the terms of any licence which may be`
  line `required for such places under any other Act:`
  line
  line `Provided further that this sub-section shall not apply to private amateur performances or to`
  line `performances held wholly for the benefit of charity, in any such place.`
  line
  line `(3) If within a period of three months following the receipt of an application for licence under`
  line `sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) the Nagar Panchayat or the Council at a meeting has not passed order`
  line `thereon, either granting or refusing a licence, it shall be deemed to have granted the licence.`
obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_170:
  sectionId (40566)
  sectionNo (170)
  orderNo 170
  title `Cancellation, revocation, etc., of licences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_170_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40566&sectionno=170&orderno=170&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_170_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 196, any`
  line `licence granted under section 169 by the municipality may, at any time, be suspended or revoked by it, if`
  line `any of the restriction, limitations or conditions attached to the licence, be evaded or infringed by the`
  line `grantee or if the grantee be convicted of a breach of any of the provisions of this Act or of any rule or`
  line `bye-law made thereunder in any matter to which such licence relates or if the grantee has obtained the`
  line `same by misrepresentation or fraud.`
obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_171:
  sectionId (40567)
  sectionNo (171)
  orderNo 171
  title `Publication of order of refusal, suspension of licences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_171_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_171_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40567&sectionno=171&orderno=171&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_171_content:
  string
  line `Every order granting, refusing,`
  line `suspending, revoking, or modifying a licence under section 169 or section 170, as the case may be, shall`
  line `be, in writing, shall state the ground on which it proceeds, shall be published on the notice board of the`
  line `office of the Nagar Panchayat or the Council and shall also be served on the owner of the premises`
  line `concerned within fourteen days of the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_171_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_172:
  sectionId (40568)
  sectionNo (172)
  orderNo 172
  title `Power to close market, tea-stall, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_172_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_172_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40568&sectionno=172&orderno=172&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_172_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Nagar Panchayat or, as the case may be, the`
  line `Council may, with a view to preventing the spread of any infectious or contagious disease, order that for a`
  line `specified time, any market, tea-stall or restaurant, hotel or lodging-house within the Municipality shall be`
  line `closed, or forbid any persons to attend any such market, tea-stall or restaurant, hotel or lodging-house.`
  line
  line `(2) Such order shall be notified in such manner and at such places as the Nagar Panchayat or the`
  line `Council may direct, and notice thereof shall be served on the owner, occupier or vendor of the market or`
  line `the keeper of the hotel or lodging-house, tea-stall or restaurant.`
  line
  line `(3) After complying with the notice to the owner or occupier, or vendor of the market or the keeper of`
  line `the hotel or lodging-house, tea-stall or restaurant or any person interested may appeal to the Deputy`
  line `Commissioner, and if he considers the notice to be unreasonable, the order of the Deputy Commissioner`
  line `shall be final.`
  line
  line `(4) When an order has been notified under sub-section (2) and has not been set aside under`
  line `sub-section (3) any owner, occupier or vendor of a market or the keeper of hotel or lodging-house,`
  line `tea-stall or restaurant who neglects to close the market, hotel or lodging-house, tea-stall or restaurant shall`
  line `be liable to a fine which may extend to five thousand rupees; and any person who attends such market,`
  line `hotel or lodging-house, tea-stall or restaurant in contravention of the terms of the order shall be liable to`
  line `fine which may extend to five hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_172_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_173:
  sectionId (40569)
  sectionNo (173)
  orderNo 173
  title `Penalty for failure to give information of cholera.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_173_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_173_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40569&sectionno=173&orderno=173&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_173_content:
  string
  line Whoever--
  line
  line `(a) being a medical practitioner and in the course of such practice becoming cognizant of the`
  line `existence of cholera, plague, small pox or other infectious disease, that may be notified in this behalf`
  line `by the Government in any dwelling-house other than a public hospital in the municipality, or`
  line
  line `(b) being the owner or occupier of such dwelling house, and being cognizant of the existence of`
  line `any such infectious disease therein, or`
  line
  line `(c) being the person in charge of, or in attendance, on a person suffering from any such infectious`
  line `disease in such dwelling-house, and being cognizant of the existence of the disease therein,`
  line
  line `fails to give information within twenty-four hours of becoming so cognizant or gives false information to`
  line `such officer as the Nagar Panchayat or as the case may be, the Council may appoint in this behalf`
  line `respecting the existence of such disease shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred`
  line rupees.
obj_root_law_sections_173_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_174:
  sectionId (40570)
  sectionNo (174)
  orderNo 174
  title `Disinfection of building and articles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_174_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40570&sectionno=174&orderno=174&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_174_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Nagar Panchayat or, as the case may be, the`
  line `Council is of opinion that the cleansing or disinfecting of a building or any part thereof or of any article`
  line `therein, which is likely to retain infection, will tend to prevent or check the spread of any disease, it may, by notice require the owner or occupier to cleanse or disinfect the same in the manner and within the time`
  line `prescribed in such notice.`
  line
  line `(2) If--`
  line
  line `(a) within the time specified as aforesaid from the receipt of the notice the person on whom the`
  line `notice is served to have the building or part thereof or the article disinfected, or`
  line
  line `(b) the occupier or owner, as the case may be, gives his consent,`
  line
  line `the Nagar Panchayat or the Council may, at the cost of such owner or occupier, cause the building or part`
  line `thereof and articles to be cleansed and disinfected:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Nagar Panchayat or the Council may, in its discretion pay the whole or any part of`
  line `such cost.`
obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_175:
  sectionId (40571)
  sectionNo (175)
  orderNo 175
  title `Penalty for letting infected house.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_175_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_175_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40571&sectionno=175&orderno=175&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_175_content:
  string
  line `Every person knowingly letting a house or other building`
  line `or part of a house or building in which any person suffering from an infectious or contagious disease, had`
  line `lived without having such house or other building or part thereof and all articles therein liable to retain`
  line `infection, disinfected thereafter to the satisfaction of the Nagar Panchayat or the Council, shall be`
  line `punishable with fine not exceeding two thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this section a hotel or lodging-house keeper shall be deemed to let`
  line `part of his house to any person admitted as a guest into his hotel or lodging-house.`
obj_root_law_sections_175_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_176:
  sectionId (40572)
  sectionNo (176)
  orderNo 176
  title `Power of entry for purpose of preventing spread of disease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_176_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_176_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40572&sectionno=176&orderno=176&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_176_content:
  string
  line `The Nagar Panchayat or, as the`
  line `case may be, the Council may authorise any officer to enter, at any time between sunrise and sunset, after`
  line `three hours notice into any building or premises in which any infectious or contagious disease is reported`
  line `or suspected to exist, for the purposes of inspecting such building or premises on the basis of the report of`
  line `the officer. The Nagar Panchayat or the Council will have the power to declare that a person is suffering`
  line `from contagious disease and that house is infectious.`
obj_root_law_sections_176_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_177:
  sectionId (40573)
  sectionNo (177)
  orderNo 177
  title `Removal to hospital of patients suffering from infectious disease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_177_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_177_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40573&sectionno=177&orderno=177&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_177_content:
  string
  line `In any municipality when`
  line `any person suffering from any infectious disease is found to be--`
  line
  line `(a) without proper lodging or accomodation, or`
  line
  line `(b) living in a Serai or other public hostel, or`
  line
  line `(c) living in a room or house which neither he nor any one, of whom he is a dependent, either`
  line `own or pays rent for,`
  line
  line `the Nagar Panchayat or, as the case may be, the Council, by any persons authorised by it in this behalf`
  line `may, on the advice of an Assistant Surgeon, remove the patient to any hospital or place at which persons`
  line `suffering from such diseases are received for medical treatment and may do anything necessary for such`
  line removal.
obj_root_law_sections_177_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_178:
  sectionId (40574)
  sectionNo (178)
  orderNo 178
  title `Municipality to provide places for recreation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_178_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_178_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40574&sectionno=178&orderno=178&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_178_content:
  string
  line `The municipality may provide open spaces,`
  line `parks, playgrounds, common swimming pools and amenities for the use and enjoyment of the people and`
  line `may frame bye-laws regulating their use.`
obj_root_law_sections_178_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_179:
  sectionId (40575)
  sectionNo (179)
  orderNo 179
  title `Function and powers in regard to pounds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_179_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_179_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40575&sectionno=179&orderno=179&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_179_content:
  string
  line `Every municipality shall, in regard to the`
  line `establishment, maintenance and management of pounds, perform such function as may be transferred to it`
  line `by notification under section 31 of the Cattle Trespass Act, 1871 (1 of 1871 ) and lease out pound, when`
  line `so transferred, according to rules framed under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_179_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_180:
  sectionId (40576)
  sectionNo (180)
  orderNo 180
  title `Service of notice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_180_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_180_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40576&sectionno=180&orderno=180&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_180_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every notice, bill, form, summons or notice of demand under this Act,`
  line may--
  line
  line `(a) be served personally on or presented to the person to whom the same is addressed; or`
  line
  line `(b) if it cannot be so served, presented or delivered, be affixed on some conspicuous part of his`
  line `place of abode or of the land, building or other thing in respect of which the notice, bill, form,`
  line `summons or notice of demand is intended to be served; or`
  line
  line `(c) be sent by post in registered cover.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such notice, bill, form, summons or notice of' demand shall be signed by or bear a facsimile`
  line `signature of Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson or any other officer authorised by the Chairperson in that`
  line behalf.
obj_root_law_sections_180_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_181:
  sectionId (40577)
  sectionNo (181)
  orderNo 181
  title `Reasonable time for act to be fixed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_181_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_181_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40577&sectionno=181&orderno=181&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_181_content:
  string
  line `When any notice under this Act requires any act to be`
  line `done for which no time is fixed by this Act, the Nagar Panchayat or Council shall fix a reasonable time`
  line `for doing the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_181_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_182:
  sectionId (40578)
  sectionNo (182)
  orderNo 182
  title `Service of notice on owner or occupier of land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_182_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_182_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40578&sectionno=182&orderno=182&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_182_content:
  string
  line `When any notice is required to be given to`
  line `the owner or to the occupier of any land, or both, such notice addressed to the owner or occupier or both,`
  line `as the case may require, may be served on the occupier of such land, or otherwise in the manner`
  line `mentioned in section 180:`
  line
  line `Provided that when the owner and his place of abode are known to the Nagar Panchayat or to the`
  line `Council or other authorities issuing the notice they shall, if such place of abode be within the limits of`
  line `their authority, cause such notice to be served on such owner, or left with some adult member or servant`
  line `of his family; and if the place of abode of the owner be not within such limits, they shall send every such`
  line `notice by post in a registered cover addressed to his place of abode and such service shall be deemed to be`
  line `good service of the notice:`
  line
  line `Provided further that when the name of the owner or occupier or of both is not known it shall be`
  line `sufficient to designate him or them as "the owner" or "the occupier" of the land in respect of which the`
  line `notice is served.`
obj_root_law_sections_182_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_183:
  sectionId (40632)
  sectionNo (183)
  orderNo 183
  title `Procedure when owners or occupiers are required by Nagar Panchayat or the Council to execute works.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_183_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_183_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40632&sectionno=183&orderno=183&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_183_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever it is provided in this Act, that the Nagar Panchayat or, the Council may`
  line `require the owner or the occupiers, of any land or both to execute any work or to do anything, such`
  line `requisition shall be made, as far as possible, by a notice to be served as provided in sections 180 and 182`
  line `on every owner or occupier who is required to execute such work or to do such thing; but if there be any`
  line `doubt as to the persons who are owners or occupiers, such requisition may be made by a notice to be`
  line `affixed or posted upon or near the spot at which the work is required to be executed or the thing done`
  line `requiring the owners or the occupiers, of any land or both, to execute such notice. It shall not be necessary`
  line `to name the owners or occupiers.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such requisition shall give notice to the persons to whom it is addressed that, if they fail to`
  line `comply with the requisition or prefer an objection against such requisition as provided hereafter in section`
  line `184 the municipality may enter upon the land and cause the required work to be executed, or the required`
  line `thing to be done; and that in such case the expenses incurred thereby shall be recovered from the persons`
  line `who are required in such requisition to execute such work or do such thing.`
obj_root_law_sections_183_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_184:
  sectionId (40580)
  sectionNo (184)
  orderNo 184
  title `Person required to execute any work may prefer objection to the municipality.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_184_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_184_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40580&sectionno=184&orderno=184&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_184_content:
  string
  line Any
  line `person who is required by such requisition to execute any work or to do anything may instead of`
  line `executing the work or doing the thing required, prefer an objection in writing to the municipality against`
  line `such requisition within fifteen days of the service of the notice affixing or posting up of the notification`
  line `containing the requisition, or if the time within which he is required to comply with the requisition be less`
  line `than fifteen days, then within such less time.`
obj_root_law_sections_184_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_185:
  sectionId (40581)
  sectionNo (185)
  orderNo 185
  title `Procedure if person objecting alleges that work will cost more than three thousand rupees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_185_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_185_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40581&sectionno=185&orderno=185&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_185_content:
  string
  line `If the objector alleges that the cost of executing the work or of doing the thing required may`
  line `exceed three thousand rupees, such objection shall be heard and disposed of by the municipality at a`
  line `meeting, unless the Chairperson or Vice-Chairperson shall certify that such cost may not exceed three`
  line `thousand rupees, in which case the objection shall be heard and disposed of by the Chairperson and the`
  line `Vice-Chairperson:`
  line
  line `Provided that in any case in which the Chairperson or the Vice-Chairperson shall have certified his`
  line `opinion and the objection shall in consequence thereof have been heard and disposed of by the Chairperson and the Vice-Chairperson, the person making the objection may, if the requisition made upon`
  line `him is not withdrawn on the hearing of his objection, pay in the said sum of three thousand rupees to the`
  line `municipality as the cost of executing the work or doing the thing required, whereupon such person shall`
  line `be relieved of all further liability and obligation, in respect of executing the work or doing the thing`
  line `required and in respect of paying the expenses thereof and the municipality itself shall execute such work`
  line `or do such thing, and shall exercise all powers necessary therefor.`
obj_root_law_sections_185_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_186:
  sectionId (40582)
  sectionNo (186)
  orderNo 186
  title `Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson to make order after hearing objection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_186_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_186_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40582&sectionno=186&orderno=186&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_186_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson or`
  line `the Vice-Chairperson, of the Nagar Panchayat or, the council as the case may be, shall after hearing the`
  line `objection and making any enquiry which they may deem necessary, record an order withdrawing,`
  line `modifying, or making absolute the requisition against which the objection is preferred and if such order`
  line `does not withdraw the requisition it shall specify the time within which the requisition shall be carried`
  line `out, which shall not be less than the shortest time which might have been mentioned in the original`
  line `requisition under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_186_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_187:
  sectionId (40583)
  sectionNo (187)
  orderNo 187
  title `Power of municipality on failure of persons to execute works.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_187_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_187_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40583&sectionno=187&orderno=187&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_187_content:
  string
  line `If the person or persons`
  line `required to execute the work or to do the thing fail, within the time specified in any requisition as`
  line `aforesaid, to begin to execute such work or to do such thing, and thereafter diligently to execute the same`
  line `to the satisfaction of the municipality until it is completed, the municipality or any person authorised by it`
  line `in that behalf, may, after giving forty-eight hours notice of its intention by a notification to be affixed or`
  line `posted upon or near the spot, enter upon the land and perform all necessary acts for the execution of the`
  line `work or doing of the thing required; and the expenses thereby incurred shall be paid by the owners or by`
  line `the occupiers, if such requisition was addressed to the owners or to the occupiers, as the case may be, and`
  line `by the owners and the occupiers, if such requisition was addressed to the owners and the occupiers.`
obj_root_law_sections_187_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_188:
  sectionId (40584)
  sectionNo (188)
  orderNo 188
  title `Power to apportion expenses among owners and occupiers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_188_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_188_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40584&sectionno=188&orderno=188&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_188_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever any expenses`
  line `incurred by the municipality are to be paid by the owners of any land as provided in section 187 the`
  line `municipality may, if there be more than one owner, apportion the said expenses among such of the`
  line `owners as are known in such manner as the municipality may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(2) Whenever any such expenses are to be paid by the occupiers of any land as provided in section`
  line `187 the municipality may, if there be more than one occupier, apportion the said expenses among such of`
  line `the occupiers, as are known in such manner as the municipality may deem fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_188_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_189:
  sectionId (40585)
  sectionNo (189)
  orderNo 189
  title `Apportionment among owners and occupiers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_189_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_189_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40585&sectionno=189&orderno=189&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_189_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any expenses incurred by the`
  line `municipality are to be paid by the owners and occupiers of any land, as provided in section 187 the`
  line `municipality may apportion the said expenses among the said owners and occupiers or such of them as`
  line `are known in such manner as the municipality may deem fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_189_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_190:
  sectionId (40586)
  sectionNo (190)
  orderNo 190
  title `Occupiers may recover cost of works executed at their expenses from owners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_190_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_190_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40586&sectionno=190&orderno=190&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_190_content:
  string
  line Whenever
  line `any works or alterations and improvements, of which the municipality is authorised by this Act to require`
  line `the execution, are executed by the occupier on the requisition of the municipality, or are executed by the`
  line `municipality and cost thereof is recovered from the occupier, the cost thereof may, if the municipality`
  line `certify that such cost ought to be borne by the owner, be deducted by such occupier from the next and`
  line `following payment of his rent due or becoming due to such owner, or may be recovered by him in any`
  line `court of competent jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_190_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_191:
  sectionId (40587)
  sectionNo (191)
  orderNo 191
  title `Power to enter upon, possession of houses so repaired.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_191_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_191_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40587&sectionno=191&orderno=191&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_191_content:
  string
  line `If the municipality under the`
  line `provisions of this Act shall have caused any repairs to be made to any house or other structure and if such`
  line `house or other structure be unoccupied, the municipality may enter into possession of the same, and may`
  line `retain possession thereof until the sum expended by it on the repairs be paid to it.`
obj_root_law_sections_191_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_192:
  sectionId (40588)
  sectionNo (192)
  orderNo 192
  title `Sale of materials of houses pulled down.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_192_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_192_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40588&sectionno=192&orderno=192&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_192_content:
  string
  line `(1) The materials of anything which shall have been`
  line `pulled down or removed under the provisions of section 183 may be sold by the municipality, and the`
  line `proceeds of such sale shall be adjusted to the payment of the expenses incurred.`
  line
  line `(2) The surplus sale-proceeds, if any, shall be credited to the Municipal fund, and may be paid on`
  line `demand to any person who establishes his right to the satisfaction of the municipality or in a court of`
  line `competent jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_192_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_193:
  sectionId (40589)
  sectionNo (193)
  orderNo 193
  title Cognizance.
  content obj_root_law_sections_193_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_193_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40589&sectionno=193&orderno=193&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_193_content:
  string
  line `(1) Unless otherwise expressly provided in this Act a Court shall take cognizance`
  line `of any offence under this Act or under any rules or bye-laws made thereunder except on the complaint of`
  line `the municipality or some person authorised by the municipality by general or special order in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) No Court inferior to that of a Magistrate of the first class shall try any of the offences specified in`
  line `sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_193_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_194:
  sectionId (40590)
  sectionNo (194)
  orderNo 194
  title `Offences under the Act compoundable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_194_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_194_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40590&sectionno=194&orderno=194&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_194_content:
  string
  line `(1) The offences under this Act shall be`
  line `compoundable:`
  line
  line `Provided that no offence, arising from the failure to comply with a written notice given by or on`
  line `behalf of, the Nagar Panchayat or the Council, as the case may be, shall be compoundable unless the`
  line `notice has been complied with.`
  line
  line `(2) Sums paid by way of composition under this section shall be credited to the Municipal Fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_194_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_195:
  sectionId (40591)
  sectionNo (195)
  orderNo 195
  title `Power and duties of police in respect of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_195_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_195_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40591&sectionno=195&orderno=195&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_195_content:
  string
  line `Every police officer shall give immediate`
  line `information to the municipality of an offence coming to his knowledge which has been committed against`
  line `this Act or against any rules or bye-laws made thereunder, and shall be bound to assist all members,`
  line `officers and employees of the municipality in the exercise of their lawful duty.`
obj_root_law_sections_195_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_196:
  sectionId (40592)
  sectionNo (196)
  orderNo 196
  title `Appeals from order refusing licences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_196_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_196_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40592&sectionno=196&orderno=196&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_196_content:
  string
  line `Any person aggrieved by an order of a municipality`
  line `refusing, revoking or suspending licence or permission required under this Act may, notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained elsewhere in this Act, within thirty days from the date of refusal, revoking or`
  line `suspension, appeal to the State Government or an officer authorised by the Government in that behalf`
  line `whose decision shall be final and shall not be questioned in any Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_196_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_197:
  sectionId (40593)
  sectionNo (197)
  orderNo 197
  title `Appeals from orders in other cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_197_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_197_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40593&sectionno=197&orderno=197&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_197_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved,--`
  line
  line `(a) by the refusal of the Nagar Panchayat or Council under section 126 to sanction the erection,`
  line `re-erection or material alteration of any building; or`
  line
  line `(b) by a notice from the Nagar Panchayat or Council under section 112 requiring a road to be`
  line `drained, levelled, paved, flagged, metalled, or provided with proper means of lighting or under`
  line `section 129 requiring the alteration or demolition of a building; or`
  line
  line `(c) by any order of the Nagar Panchayat or Council under the powers conferred upon it by section`
  line `132 or by any order made by the Nagar Panchayat or by the Council under bye-law framed under`
  line `clause (vii) of sub-section (1) of section 209,`
  line
  line `may, within thirty days from the date of such refusal, notice, order, appeal to the Deputy Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(2) No such refusal, notice or order shall be questioned otherwise than by such an appeal.`
  line
  line `(3) The decision of the Deputy Commissioner shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_197_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_198:
  sectionId (40594)
  sectionNo (198)
  orderNo 198
  title `Appeal not to be dismissed without giving reasonable opportunity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_198_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_198_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40594&sectionno=198&orderno=198&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_198_content:
  string
  line `No appeal under`
  line `section 196 or section 197 shall be dismissed or allowed partly or wholly, unless reasonable opportunity`
  line `of showing cause or being heard has been given to the parties.`
obj_root_law_sections_198_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_199:
  sectionId (40595)
  sectionNo (199)
  orderNo 199
  title `Dispute as to compensation payable by municipality.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_199_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_199_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40595&sectionno=199&orderno=199&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_199_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a dispute arises regarding`
  line `the amount of compensation which the municipality is required by this Act to pay, it shall be settled in`
  line `such manner as the parties may agree, in default of agreement, by the Deputy Commissioner upon`
  line `application made to him by the municipality or the person claiming compensation.`
  line
  line `(2) If the municipality or the person claiming compensation is not satisfied with the decision of the`
  line `Deputy Commissioner, it or he shall have a right to require the Deputy Commissioner to make a reference`
  line `to the District Judge, in accordance with the provisions of section 18 of the Land Acquisition Act, 1894`
  line `(1 of 1894 ).`
obj_root_law_sections_199_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_200:
  sectionId (40596)
  sectionNo (200)
  orderNo 200
  title Indemnity.
  content obj_root_law_sections_200_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_200_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40596&sectionno=200&orderno=200&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_200_content:
  string
  line `No suit shall be maintainable against Nagar Panchayat or Council or any of its`
  line `committees, or any officer or employee, or any person acting under or in accordance with, the direction of`
  line `the Nagar Panchayat or of the Council or any of its committees or any municipal officer or servant, in`
  line `respect of anything in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act or under any rule or bye-law`
  line `made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_200_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_201:
  sectionId (40597)
  sectionNo (201)
  orderNo 201
  title `Bar of suits in absence of notice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_201_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_201_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40597&sectionno=201&orderno=201&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_201_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit or other legal proceeding, not being a criminal`
  line `proceeding, shall be instituted against any Nagar Panchayat or Council, or any of its officers in respect of`
  line `any act purporting to be done by such officer in his official capacity, or any person acting under its`
  line `direction, until the expiry of two months next after notice in writing has been delivered to or left at the`
  line `office of--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a suit against the Nagar Panchayat or Council, the Executive Officer;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of an officer, the officer against whom the suit or proceeding is instituted and, in`
  line `the case of any person acting under its direction, delivered to him at his place of residence or business`
  line `stating the cause of action, the name, description and place of residence of the plaintiff or the`
  line `petitioner and the relief which he claims; and the plaint or the petition shall contain a statement that`
  line `such notice has been so delivered or left.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section "Officer" includes the Chairperson and the Vice-Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such action shall be commenced within three months next after the arising of the cause of`
  line `action, and not afterwards.`
obj_root_law_sections_201_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_202:
  sectionId (40598)
  sectionNo (202)
  orderNo 202
  title `Control by Deputy Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_202_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_202_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40598&sectionno=202&orderno=202&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_202_content:
  string
  line `The Deputy Commissioner or the Director or any officer`
  line `so empowered by the Government in this behalf may at any time--`
  line
  line `(i) enter into and inspect, or cause any other person to enter into or inspect--`
  line
  line `(a) any immovable property in the occupation of, or`
  line
  line `(b) any work in progress under, or`
  line
  line `(c) any institution under the control and administration of the Nagar Panchayat, or as the case`
  line `may be, the Council; and`
  line
  line `(ii) call for inspection of any book or document which may be, for the purpose of this Act, in the`
  line `possession or under the control of the Nagar Panchayat or, as the case may be, the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_202_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_203:
  sectionId (40599)
  sectionNo (203)
  orderNo 203
  title `Power to suspend action under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_203_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_203_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40599&sectionno=203&orderno=203&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_203_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Government, or the Deputy Commissioner`
  line `may, by order in writing, suspend the execution of any resolution or order of the municipality or prohibit`
  line `the doing of any act which is about to be done or is being done, in pursuance of, or under this Act, or in`
  line `pursuance of any sanction or permission granted by the municipality in the exercise of their powers under`
  line `this Act, if in its or his opinion, the resolution, order or act is contrary to the public interest or is in excess`
  line `of the powers conferred by law, or the execution of the resolution or order, or the doing of the act is likely`
  line `to lead to a serious breach of the peace, or to cause serious injury or annoyance to the public, or to any`
  line `class or body of persons.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Deputy Commissioner makes any order under this section, he shall forthwith forward a`
  line `copy thereof, with a statement of his reasons for making it, to the Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Government may obtain the views of the Director and thereupon either rescind the order or`
  line `direct that it continues in force with such modification and for such period as it may deem fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_203_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_204:
  sectionId (40600)
  sectionNo (204)
  orderNo 204
  title `Powers of Deputy Commissioner in case of emergency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_204_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_204_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40600&sectionno=204&orderno=204&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_204_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, in any case of emergency, the`
  line `Deputy Commissioner upon the recommendation of the concerned technical advisor immediately,`
  line `available, is of opinion that the immediate execution of any work or the immediate doing of any act which`
  line `the Nagar Panchayat or the Council, whether at a meeting or otherwise, are empowered to execute or do,`
  line `is necessary for the health or safety of the public, he may call upon the Nagar Panchayat or the Council to`
  line `execute the work within such time as he may appoint. If such work is not executed within such period he`
  line `may appoint some other person to execute the work or do the act immediately.`
  line
  line `(2) The Deputy Commissioner shall forthwith report to the Government every case in which he uses`
  line `the powers conferred on him under sub-section (1) whereupon the Government may pass such order as it`
  line `may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any person is appointed under sub-section (1), the Deputy Commissioner may direct that`
  line `the expense of performing the duty, executing the work or doing the act, together with reasonable remuneration, if any, to the person so appointed, shall forthwith be paid by the Nagar Panchayat or by the`
  line Council.
  line
  line `(4) Where such expense and remuneration are not so paid, the Deputy Commissioner may make an`
  line `order directing the person having the custody of the balance of the Municipal Fund to pay the expense and`
  line `remuneration, or so much thereof as is possible from the balance, in priority to any or all other charge,`
  line `and such person shall make payment accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_204_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_205:
  sectionId (40601)
  sectionNo (205)
  orderNo 205
  title `Power to dissolve Nagar Panchayat or Council in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_205_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_205_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40601&sectionno=205&orderno=205&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_205_content:
  string
  line `If in the opinion of the`
  line `Government, a Nagar Panchayat or a Council, as the case may be, is not competent to perform or`
  line `persistently make default in the performance of the obligatory duties imposed upon it by or under this Act`
  line `or exceed or abuse its power the Government may by notification, stating the reasons for so doing declare`
  line `such Nagar Panchayat or Council to be incompetent or in default or to have exceeded or abused its power,`
  line `as the case may be, and dissolve such Nagar Panchayat or Council:`
  line
  line `Provided that a Nagar Panchayat or a Council, as the case may be, shall be given a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard before its dissolution:`
  line
  line `Provided further that when a Nagar Panchayat or a Council, as the case may be, is dissolved, the`
  line `Government may appoint any person or persons to exercise and perform the powers and duties of the`
  line `Nagar Panchayat or the Council during the period of dissolution until the new Nagar Panchayat or the`
  line `Council, as the case may be, is constituted:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the Government shall, before the expiry of a period of six months from the date of`
  line `dissolution of the Nagar Panchayat or the Council, cause fresh elections to be held for the constitution of`
  line `a new Nagar Panchayat or a new Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_205_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_206:
  sectionId (40602)
  sectionNo (206)
  orderNo 206
  title `Consequence of dissolution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_206_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_206_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40602&sectionno=206&orderno=206&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_206_content:
  string
  line `An order of dissolution shall have the following consequences,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) all the Councillors of the Nagar Panchayat or of the Council shall, as from the date of order,`
  line `vacate their offices as such Councillors;`
  line
  line `(b) all the powers and duties which under the Act may be exercised and performed by the Nagar`
  line `Panchayat or the Council, whether at a meeting or otherwise, shall, during the period of dissolution,`
  line `be exercised and performed by such person or persons as the Government may direct;`
  line
  line `(c) all property vested in such Nagar Panchayat or the Council shall, during the period of`
  line `dissolution, vest in the Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_206_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_207:
  sectionId (40603)
  sectionNo (207)
  orderNo 207
  title `Decision of disputes between local authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_207_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_207_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40603&sectionno=207&orderno=207&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_207_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a dispute arises between a Nagar`
  line `Panchayat or a Council or any other local authority on any matter which they are jointly interested, such`
  line `dispute shall be referred to Government, whose decision shall be final.`
  line
  line `(2) The Government may regulate by rules made under this Act the relation to be observed between a`
  line `Nagar Panchayat or a Council and other local authorities in any matter in which they are jointly`
  line interested.
obj_root_law_sections_207_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_208:
  sectionId (40604)
  sectionNo (208)
  orderNo 208
  title `Powers of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_208_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_208_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40604&sectionno=208&orderno=208&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_208_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Government may, by notification and`
  line `subject to the condition of previous publication, make rules for the purpose of carrying into effect the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) manner in which the minutes of the proceedings of a meeting of a Nagar Panchayat or a`
  line `Council or its committees shall be recorded and published;`
  line
  line `(ii) form and manner in which the accounts of receipts and expenditures of a Nagar Panchayat or`
  line `a Council shall be kept;`
  line
  line `(iii) form and manner in which the annual budget of a Nagar Panchayat or a Council shall be`
  line prepared;
  line
  line `(iv) manner in which returns, statements and reports by a Nagar Panchayat or a Council shall be`
  line submitted;
  line
  line `(v) matter not specifically provided for in this Act for the valuation of holdings, for the`
  line `assessment, collection and refund of taxes imposed under this Act;`
  line
  line `(vi) determination of fees payable upon distraint warrant under this Act;`
  line
  line `(vii) regulation, management and inspection of the working systems of water-supply, lighting,`
  line `drainage or sewerage provided, established or maintained by or under the control and administration`
  line `of a Nagar Panchayat or a Council;`
  line
  line `(viii) form and procedure for taking oath or affirmation by Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson and`
  line `Councillor the authority who shall administer oath or affirmation; and`
  line
  line `(ix) manner in which bye-laws shall be published after confirmation by the Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before Legislative`
  line `Assembly while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or`
  line `in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session in which it is so laid or the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, Legislative Assembly`
  line `makes any modification in the rule or decides that any such rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_208_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_209:
  sectionId (40605)
  sectionNo (209)
  orderNo 209
  title `Power of municipality to frame bye-laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_209_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_209_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40605&sectionno=209&orderno=209&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_209_content:
  string
  line `(1) A municipality may, frame bye-laws consistent`
  line `with the provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder for carrying out the provisions of this Act,`
  line for--
  line
  line `(i) any matter in respect of which power to frame bye-laws is conferred expressely on the`
  line `municipalilty under this Act;`
  line
  line `(ii) regulating traffic, and preventing obstructions and encroachments and unisances on or near`
  line `public roads, or on or near pontoons bridges, ghats, landing places, river banks or other places of`
  line `public resort or on places near water works for the supply of drinking water;`
  line
  line `(iii) prescribing a minimum width of wheel-tyres or a minimum diameter and the maximum`
  line `wheel-tracks or wheels for different classes of carts and carriage kept or used within the municipality;`
  line
  line `(iv) prescribing the manner in which notice of the intention to erect, re-erect, materially alter a`
  line `building shall be given to the municipality;`
  line
  line `(v) requiring that with every such notice shall be furnished with a site-plan of the land on which it`
  line `is intended to erect, re-erect or materially alter such building and plan and specification, and in the`
  line `case of erection or re-erection of a building, estimate also of the cost of construction (excluding cost`
  line `of land and its improvement) of the building, all such characters and with such details as the`
  line `bye-laws may require in respect of all or any of the following matters, viz.--`
  line
  line `(a) free passage or way in front of the building;`
  line
  line `(b) space to be left about the building to secure free circulation of air and facilitate`
  line `scavenging and for the prevention of fire;`
  line
  line `(c) provision and position of latrines, privies, urinals, cesspools or drains;`
  line
  line `(d) level and width of foundation, level of the lowest floor, and stability of the structure; and`
  line
  line `(e) the line of frontage with neighbouring buildings, it the building abuts on a public road;`
  line
  line `(vi) regulating in respect of the erection, re-erection or material alteration of any buildings, within`
  line `the municipality or part thereof--`
  line
  line `(a) the materials and method of construction to be used for external and partition walls, roofs`
  line `and floors;`
  line
  line `(b) the materials and method of construction and position of fire-places, chimneys, latrines,`
  line `privies, urinals, cesspools and drains;`
  line
  line `(c) the height and slope of the roof above the uppermost floor upon which human beings are`
  line `to live or cooking operations are to be carried on;`
  line
  line `(d) the space to be left about the building to secure the free circulation of air and for the`
  line `prevention of fire;`
  line
  line `(e) the line of frontage where the building abuts on a public road;`
  line
  line `(f) the number and height of the storeys of which the building may consist;`
  line
  line `(g) the means to be provided for egress from the building in case of fire;`
  line
  line `(h) any other matter affecting the ventilation or sanitation of the building; and`
  line
  line `(i) matter concerning sanitary conditions and water pollution of the area;`
  line
  line `(vii) preventing the erection of buildings without adequate provisions being made for the laying`
  line `out and location of roads;`
  line
  line `(viii) regulating the level, means of drainage, alignment and width of roads constructed by private`
  line persons;
  line
  line `(ix) regulating the use of, and the prevention of nuisance in regard to public water-supply, bathing`
  line `and washing place, streams, channels, tanks and wells;`
  line
  line `(x) regulating, either by granting licences necessary or otherwise, the washing of clothes by`
  line `professional washerman, and fixing the places in which clothes may be so washed or in which they`
  line `may not be so washed;`
  line
  line `(xi) prescribing the measures to be taken for the prevention of the breeding of mosquitoes in`
  line `wells, tanks, pools, excavations, cisterns or other places or vessels containing or capable of containing`
  line water;
  line
  line `(xii) regulating the cutting of trees and bamboos within the municipality;`
  line
  line `(xiii) regulating the disposal of sewage, offensive matter, carcasses of animals and rubbish, and`
  line `the construction and maintenance of latrines, privies, urinals, cesspools, drains and sewers;`
  line
  line `(xiv) providing for the inspection and regulation of markets and for the preparation and exhibition`
  line `of a price list thereat;`
  line
  line `(xv) regulating the hours and manner of transport within the municipality of any specified articles`
  line `of food or drink;`
  line
  line `(xvi) fixing the places in which any specified article of food or drink may be sold or exposed for`
  line `sale or the places in which it may not be sold or exposed for sale and regulating the sale of foodstaff`
  line `unfit for human consumption;`
  line
  line `(xvii) regulating either by granting licences necessary or otherwise, or prohibiting, for the purpose`
  line `of preventing danger to the public health the stalling or herding of horses, cattle, swine, donkeys,`
  line `sheep or goats, geese, ducks and fowls;`
  line
  line `(xviii) providing for the inspection of milch cattle and prescribing the measures to be taken on the`
  line `occurrence among them of infections or contagious diseases; and prescribing and regulating the`
  line `construction, dimensions, ventilation, lighting, cleansing drainage and water-supply of dairies and`
  line `cattle-sheds in the occupation of persons carrying on the trade of dairymen or milksellers;`
  line
  line `(xix) providing for the inspection and proper regulation of encamping grounds, pounds, serais, or`
  line `dharmsalas; bakeries and serated water factories, ice factories, flour mills, oil mills, sweet-meat`
  line `shops, factories and other places in which mechanical or electrical power is employed, and`
  line `slaughter house;`
  line
  line `(xx) preventing nuisances affecting the public health, safety, or convenience in places of public`
  line `resort for purposes of recreation or amusement;`
  line
  line `(xxi) preventing nuisances affecting the public health, safety or convenience;`
  line
  line `(xxii) controlling and regulating the use and management of burial and burning grounds and the`
  line `disposal of corpses;`
  line
  line `(xxiii) providing for the holding of fairs and industrial exhibitions within the municipality or`
  line `under the control of the municipality and for fixing and collecting the fees to be levied thereat;`
  line
  line `(xxiv) fixing the conditions on which licences under this Act are to be granted and may be`
  line `suspended or revoked;`
  line
  line `(xxv) preventing and removing any encroachments on any municipal land including markets,`
  line `drains, roads, etc.;`
  line
  line `(xxvi) giving effect to the objects and purposes of this Act and the Municipality may by such`
  line `bye-laws impose on offenders against any provision of the bye-laws, such reasonable penalties as it`
  line `may think fit, not continuing offence, a further penalty not exceeding two hundred rupees for each`
  line `day after written notice of the offence to them from the municipality:`
  line
  line `Provided that the above limits of rupees five thousand and rupees two hundred shall not apply to`
  line `the offences in respect of the bye-laws regulating octroi;`
  line
  line `(xxvii) distribution of works among the officers and the members of the staff of the municipality.`
obj_root_law_sections_209_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_210:
  sectionId (40606)
  sectionNo (210)
  orderNo 210
  title `Additional power to frame bye-laws in hill areas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_210_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_210_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40606&sectionno=210&orderno=210&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_210_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Nagar Panchayat or Council whose`
  line `municipality is wholly or in part situated in a hilly tract may, in addition to such bye-laws as it may make`
  line `under the preceding section frame bye-laws for regulating or prohibiting the cutting or destroying of tree;`
  line `or shrubs or the making of excavations or removal of soil or quarrying, where such regulation or`
  line `prohibition appears to the Nagar Panchayat or the Council to be necessary for any or all of following`
  line `purposes:--`
  line
  line `(a) the maintenance of water supply;`
  line
  line `(b) the preservation of the soil;`
  line
  line `(c) the prevention of landslips;`
  line
  line `(d) the formation of ravines or torrents;`
  line
  line `(e) the protection of land against erosion or the deposit thereon of sand, gravel or stones;`
  line
  line `(f) the protection of the beauty or general appearance of the municipality.`
  line
  line `(2) The Nagar Panchayat or the Council may, by any bye-law framed under this section, declare that`
  line `any person commiting a breach of any such bye-law, or failing to comply with any notice issued`
  line `thereunder, shall be liable to fine which may extend to five hundred rupees and to a further fine, which`
  line `may extend to two hundred rupees for each day after conviction during which the offence is continued.`
obj_root_law_sections_210_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_211:
  sectionId (40607)
  sectionNo (211)
  orderNo 211
  title `Confirmation of bye-laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_211_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_211_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40607&sectionno=211&orderno=211&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_211_content:
  string
  line `(1) The power to frame bye-laws in the Act shall be subject to the`
  line `condition of previous notification.`
  line
  line `(2) No such bye-laws shall come into force until it has been confirmed by the Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Government may cancel its confirmation of any such bye law, and thereupon the bye-law`
  line `shall cease to have effect.`
obj_root_law_sections_211_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_212:
  sectionId (40608)
  sectionNo (212)
  orderNo 212
  title `Publication of bye-laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_212_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_212_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40608&sectionno=212&orderno=212&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_212_content:
  string
  line `Every bye-law shall, after confirmation, be published in the`
  line `prescribed manner.`
obj_root_law_sections_212_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_213:
  sectionId (40609)
  sectionNo (213)
  orderNo 213
  title `Model bye-laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_213_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_213_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40609&sectionno=213&orderno=213&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_213_content:
  string
  line `The Government may from time to time frame model bye-laws for any`
  line `matter in respect of which a municipality is empowered to frame bye-laws under this Act and publish`
  line `them in the Official Gazette for the guidance of municipality.`
obj_root_law_sections_213_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_214:
  sectionId (40610)
  sectionNo (214)
  orderNo 214
  title `Validity of acts and proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_214_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_214_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40610&sectionno=214&orderno=214&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_214_content:
  string
  line `(1) No act of the Nagar Panchayat or of the Council or of`
  line `any of its committees shall be deemed to be invalid by reason of any vacancy in the membership thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) Any proceeding of a meeting of the Nagar Panchayat or of Council or of any committee thereof`
  line `shall be valid notwithstanding that it is subsequently discovered that some person who was not entitled to`
  line `do so, sat or voted or otherwise took part in the proceedings.`
obj_root_law_sections_214_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_215:
  sectionId (40611)
  sectionNo (215)
  orderNo 215
  title `Petition for challenging election.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_215_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_215_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40611&sectionno=215&orderno=215&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_215_content:
  string
  line `(1) The election of a person to the office of a Councillor`
  line `shall not be called in question except by a petition to be filed before the Election Tribunal within such`
  line `time and in such manner as may be prescribed, on the ground that--`
  line
  line `(a) the election has not been a free election by reason that the corrupt practice of bribery or undue`
  line `influence has extensively prevailed at the election; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the result of the election has been materially affected--`
  line
  line `(i) by the improper acceptance or rejection of any nomination; or`
  line
  line `(ii) by gross failure to comply with the provisions of this Act or the rules framed thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) The Election Tribunal constituted under section 103 of the Manipur Panchayati Raj Act, 1994`
  line `(26 of 1994), shall also be the Election Tribunal for the purposes of sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) The decision of the Election Tribunal shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_215_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_216:
  sectionId (40612)
  sectionNo (216)
  orderNo 216
  title `Power to make rules for election and election petition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_216_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_216_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40612&sectionno=216&orderno=216&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_216_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of election of`
  line `Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson and Councillor, the Government shall make rules for election and election`
  line `petition under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_216_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_217:
  sectionId (40613)
  sectionNo (217)
  orderNo 217
  title `Bar of jurisdiction of Civil Courts in election matters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_217_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_217_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40613&sectionno=217&orderno=217&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_217_content:
  string
  line `(1) No civil court shall have`
  line `jurisdiction to question the legality of any action taken or any decision given by an officer or authority`
  line `appointed under this Act, in connection with the conduct of elections thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) the validity of any law relating to the delimitation of constituencies or the allotment of seats to`
  line `such constituencies, made or purporting to be made under this Act shall not be called in question in`
  line `any Court;`
  line
  line `(b) no election to any municipality shall be called in question except by an election petition`
  line `presented to Election Tribunal and in such manner as is provided for by this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_217_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_218:
  sectionId (40614)
  sectionNo (218)
  orderNo 218
  title `Election to the municipalities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_218_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_218_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40614&sectionno=218&orderno=218&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_218_content:
  string
  line `(1) The superintendence, direction and control of the`
  line `preparation of electoral rolls for, and conduct of, all elections to the Municipalities shall be vested in the`
  line `State Election Commission constituted under section 98 of the Manipur Panchayati Raj Act, 1994`
  line `(26 of 1994 ).`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of this Act, election to the municipality shall be held in accordance with`
  line `the rules made by the Government in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) The Government shall, when so requested by the State Election Commission, make available to`
  line `the State Election Commission such staff as may be necessary for the discharge of the functions conferred`
  line `on the State Election Commission under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_218_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_219:
  sectionId (40615)
  sectionNo (219)
  orderNo 219
  title `Electoral roll for a municipal area.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_219_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_219_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40615&sectionno=219&orderno=219&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_219_content:
  string
  line `(1) For every municipal area, there shall be an electoral`
  line `roll showing the names of persons qualifying to vote.`
  line
  line `(2) The electoral roll for every municipal area shall be divided into several parts, one for each ward of`
  line `a municipal area.`
  line
  line `(3) The electoral roll for a municipal area shall be prepared, revised or corrected by the State Election`
  line `Commission in accordance with such rules as may be made by the Government in this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that there shall be a preliminary publication of such electoral roll after preparation or`
  line `revision to be followed by final publication after hearing of objections in the manner prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the electoral roll for the time being in force for`
  line `the election of Members of the Manipur Legistive Assembly, so far as it relates to the area comprised in`
  line `the municipal area, may be adopted as the electoral roll for that municipal area for the purposes of`
  line `preliminary publication.`
obj_root_law_sections_219_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_220:
  sectionId (40616)
  sectionNo (220)
  orderNo 220
  title `Conditions for registration as a voter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_220_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_220_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40616&sectionno=220&orderno=220&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_220_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who--`
  line
  line `(a) is not less than 18 years of age on the qualifying date, and`
  line
  line `(b) is ordinarily resident in a municipal area,`
  line
  line `shall be entitled to be registered in the electoral roll for that municipal area.`
  line
  line `(2) No person shall be entitled to be registered in the electoral roll for any municipal area in more`
  line `than one place.`
  line
  line `(3) No person shall be entitled to be registered in the electoral roll for any municipal area if his name`
  line `has already been registered as a voter in the electoral roll of any other local authority.`
  line
  line `Explanation I.--The expression "qualifying date" shall mean such date as the Government may by`
  line `notification specify for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation II.--The expression "ordinarily resident" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it`
  line `in section 20 of the Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950).`
obj_root_law_sections_220_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_221:
  sectionId (40617)
  sectionNo (221)
  orderNo 221
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_221_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_221_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40617&sectionno=221&orderno=221&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_221_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Government may, by order do anything not inconsistent with the provisions thereof which`
  line `appears to it to be necessary or expedient for the purpose of removing the difficulty.`
obj_root_law_sections_221_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_222:
  sectionId (40618)
  sectionNo (222)
  orderNo 222
  title `Overriding effect of the provisions of the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_222_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_222_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40618&sectionno=222&orderno=222&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_222_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act, rules and`
  line `bye-laws, and orders made and directions issued thereunder shall have effect notwithstanding anything`
  line `inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force or any instrument having`
  line `effect by virtue of any such law.`
obj_root_law_sections_222_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_223:
  sectionId (40619)
  sectionNo (223)
  orderNo 223
  title `Mode of proof of municipal record and fee for certified copy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_223_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_223_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40619&sectionno=223&orderno=223&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_223_content:
  string
  line `(1) A copy of any receipt,`
  line `application, plan, notice, order, entry in a register or other document in the possession of a Nagar`
  line `Panchayat or a Council, shall, if duly certified by any person authorised by any bye-law in this behalf, be`
  line `received as evidence of the existence of any entry or document and shall be admitted as evidence of the`
  line `matters and transactions therein recorded in every case, where and to the same extent as, the original entry`
  line `or document would, if produced, have been admissible to prove such matters.`
  line
  line `(2) For the issue of such copies the Nagar Panchayat or as the case may be, the Council may impose`
  line `such fees as may be fixed by any bye-law in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_223_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_224:
  sectionId (40620)
  sectionNo (224)
  orderNo 224
  title `Restriction on the summoning of municipal servants to produce documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_224_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_224_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40620&sectionno=224&orderno=224&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_224_content:
  string
  line `No municipal`
  line `officer or servant shall in any legal proceeding to which a Nagar Panchayat or a Council is not a party be`
  line `required to produce any register or document the contents of which can be proved by a certified copy, or`
  line `to appear as a witness to prove the matters and transaction recorded therein unless by order of the court`
  line `made for a special cause.`
obj_root_law_sections_224_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_225:
  sectionId (40621)
  sectionNo (225)
  orderNo 225
  title `Penalty for violating the provision of this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_225_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_225_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40621&sectionno=225&orderno=225&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_225_content:
  string
  line `If any person violates any of the provisions of`
  line `this Act for which a penalty is not already provided under this Act, he shall be liable to a fine not`
  line `exceeding rupees five hundred for each day in the case of continuing violation.`
obj_root_law_sections_225_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_226:
  sectionId (40622)
  sectionNo (226)
  orderNo 226
  title `Public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_226_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_226_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40622&sectionno=226&orderno=226&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_226_content:
  string
  line `Every Councillor and every officer or servant of the Nagar Panchayat or the`
  line `Council and every contractor or agent appointed by it for the collection of any tax or every person`
  line `employed by such contractor or agent for collection of such tax shall be deemed to be a public servant`
  line `within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_226_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_227:
  sectionId (40623)
  sectionNo (227)
  orderNo 227
  title `District Planning Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_227_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_227_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40623&sectionno=227&orderno=227&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_227_content:
  string
  line `(1) The District Planning Committee constituted under section`
  line `96 of the Manipur Panchayati Raj Act, 1994 (26 of 1994) shall also be the District Planning Committee`
  line `for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The District Planning Committee shall consist--`
  line
  line `(a) members of House of the People who represent the whole or part of the district;`
  line
  line `(b) all the members of the State Legislative Assembly whose constituencies lie within the district;`
  line
  line `(c) Adhyaksha of the Zilla Parishad;`
  line
  line `(d) Mayor or the President of the Municipal Corpoaration or the Municipal Council respectively,`
  line
  line `having jurisdiction over the headquarters of the District; and`
  line
  line `Explanation--For the purposes of this clause, "Mayor or the President" shall mean the`
  line `Chairperson of the Municipal Council or, as the case may be, of the Municipal Corporation;`
  line
  line `(e) such number of persons not less than four-fifth of the total number of members of the`
  line `Committee as may be specified by the Government elected in the prescribed manner from amongst`
  line `the members of the Zilla Parishad, Nagar Panchayat and Councillors of the Municipal Corporation`
  line `and the Municipal Councils in the district, in proportion to the ratio between the population of the`
  line `rural areas and of the urban areas in the district.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairman of the District Co-operative Banks and of the Development Bank shall be`
  line `permanent invitees of the Committee.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chief Executive Officers shall be the Secretary of the Committee.`
  line
  line `(5) The Deputy Commissioner for the Districts shall be the Chairman District Planning Committee.`
  line
  line `(6) The District Planning Committee shall consolidate the plans prepared by the Zilla Parishad, Gram`
  line `Panchayat, Nagar Panchayat, Municipal Council and the Municipal Corporation in the district and prepare`
  line `a draft development plan for the district as a whole.`
  line
  line `(7) Every District Planning Committee shall in preparing the draft development plan--`
  line
  line `(a) have regard to--`
  line
  line `(i) the matters of common interest between the Zilla Parishad, Gram Panchayats, Nagar`
  line `Panchayats, Municipal Corporation and Municipal Councils in the district including spatial`
  line `planning sharing of water and other physical and natural resource, the integrated development of`
  line `infrastructure and environmental conservation,`
  line
  line `(ii) the extent and type of available resources whether financial or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(b) consult such institutions and organisations as the Government may by order specify.`
  line
  line `(8) The Chairman of every District Planning Committee shall forward the development plan, as`
  line `recommended by such Committee to the Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_227_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_228:
  sectionId (40624)
  sectionNo (228)
  orderNo 228
  title `Committee for Metropolitan Planning.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_228_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_228_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40624&sectionno=228&orderno=228&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_228_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Governor may by notification notify an area`
  line `having a population of ten lakh or more comprised in one or more districts and consisting of two or more`
  line `municipalities or panchayats or other contiguous areas, to be a Metropolitan area for the purposes of this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(2) On such notification the Government shall constitute in every Metropolitan area a Metropolitan`
  line `Planning Committee to prepare a draft development plan for the Metropolitan area as a whole.`
  line
  line `(3) The Government may prescribe by notification with respect to--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which the seats in such Committee shall be filled:`
  line
  line `Provided that not less than two-thirds of the members of such Committee shall be elected by, and`
  line `from amongst, the elected members of the municipalities and Chairpersons of the Panchayats in the`
  line `Metropolitan area in proportion to the ratio between the population of the municipalities and of the`
  line `Panchayats in that area;`
  line
  line `(b) the representation in such Committee of the Government of India and the Government and of`
  line `such organisations and institutions as may be deemed necessary for carrying out the functions`
  line `assigned to such Committee;`
  line
  line `(c) the functions relating to planning and co-ordination for the Metropolitan area which may be`
  line `assigned to such Committee;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner in which the Chairperson of such Committee shall be chosen.`
  line
  line `(4) Every Metropolitan Planning Committee shall, in preparing the draft development plan--`
  line
  line `(a) have regard to--`
  line
  line `(i) the plans prepared by the municipalities and the Panchayats in the Metropolitan area;`
  line
  line `(ii) matters of common interest between the municipalities and the Panchayats, including`
  line `coordinated spatial planning of the area, sharing of water and other physical and natural`
  line `resources, the integrated development of infrastructure and environmental conservation;`
  line
  line `(iii) the overall objectives and priorities set by the Government of India and the Government;`
  line
  line `(iv) the extent and nature of investments likely to be made in the Metropolitan area by`
  line `agencies of the Government of India and Government, and other available resources whether`
  line `financial or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(b) consult such institutions and organisations as the Governor may, by order, specify.`
  line
  line `(5) The Chairperson of every Metropolitan Planning Committee shall forward the development plan,`
  line `as recommended by such Committee, to the Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_228_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_229:
  sectionId (40625)
  sectionNo (229)
  orderNo 229
  title `Delegation of powers of State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_229_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_229_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40625&sectionno=229&orderno=229&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_229_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may, by notification`
  line `delegate to any officer or authority subordinate to it any of the powers conferred on it or on any officer`
  line `subordinate to it by this Act, other than powers to make rules, to be exercised, subject to such restrictions`
  line `and conditions as may be specified in the said notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_229_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_230:
  sectionId (40626)
  sectionNo (230)
  orderNo 230
  title `Repeal of Manipur Act 26 of 1976 and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_230_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_230_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40626&sectionno=230&orderno=230&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_230_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the date of the commencement of this`
  line `Act, the Manipur Municipalities Act, 1976 shall be deemed to have been repealed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the said repeal shall not affect:--`
  line
  line `(a) the validity, effect or consequence of anything done or suffered under the said enactment;`
  line
  line `(b) any right, title, obligation or liability already acquired, accrued or incurred under the said`
  line `enactment or any remedy or proceeding in respect thereof;`
  line
  line `(c) any release or discharge of or from any debt, penalty, obligation, liability, claim or demand, or`
  line `any indemnity already granted;`
  line
  line `(d) any investigation, legal proceeding or remedy in respect of any such right, privilege,`
  line `obligation, liability, penalty, forfeiture or punishment as aforesaid; and any such investigation, legal`
  line `proceeding or remedy may be instituted or enforced and any such penalty, forfeiture or punishment`
  line `may be imposed as if such enactment or part thereof had not been repealed; and`
  line
  line `(e) the operation of the said enactment in relation to areas falling within the Municipal limits of`
  line Moreh.
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), all municipalities declared, limits defined,`
  line `regulations and divisions made, all rules and bye-laws, notifications, orders, appointments and`
  line `assessments made, licences and notices, issued, taxes, tolls, rates and fees imposed or assessed, budgets`
  line `passed, plans approved, permissions or sanctions granted, contracts entered into, suits instituted and`
  line `proceedings taken under the Manipur Municipal Act, 1976 (Manipur Act 26 of 1976 ) in force`
  line `immediately before the commencement of this Act shall continue to be in force and shall be deemed to`
  line `have been respectively made, issued, imposed or assessed, passed, approved, granted, entered into,`
  line `instituted and taken under this Act until new provisions are made or superseded by anything done or any`
  line `action taken under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_230_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_231:
  sectionId (40627)
  sectionNo (231)
  orderNo 231
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_231_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_231_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737&sectionId=40627&sectionno=231&orderno=231&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00016_199443_1517807323737
obj_root_law_sections_231_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Manipur Municipalities Ordinance, 1994 (Ord. 6 of 1994) is`
  line `hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the said Ordinance shall be`
  line `deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_231_footnotes:
  string
  line
